title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix egg, garlic, onion and celery powder or salt using fastest speed on blender.
Add lemon and oil very slowly.
Start with a drop at a time.
Add Roquefort cheese until dressing reaches desired consistency.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend oil and vinegar in large mixing bowl at medium speed of mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended. Refrigerate in covered container.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut unpeeled apples into 1/4 to 1/2-inch chunks and drop into a large bowl.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apples and mix thoroughly (this keeps apples from discoloring).
Add the celery, raisins and walnuts; stir.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise and milk to suit your taste.
Mix until smooth, then stir into salad mixture, tossing well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add unthawed berries and stir until berries are separated.
Add undrained pineapple and bananas; mix well.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into 9-inch pan. Chill until set.
Let remaining gelatin mixture stand at room temperature.
Whip together sour cream and cream cheese in bowl. Spread over first gelatin layer.
Top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until set.
Fold whipped cream into mayonnaise. Top salad with mayonnaise mixture.

title: pineapple dreamsicle punch
directions: Pour pineapple juice and ginger ale over ice cream and sherbet.
Stir until ice cream has melted and blended.
Makes 24 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a greased 9-inch square dish break up hamburger.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and chopped onion.
Pour both cans of cheese soup over this.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Butter 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Place broccoli in bottom of dish (rinse broccoli in hot water and drain first).
Place cooked chicken over broccoli.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder, and pour over chicken.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Top cheese with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (sometimes longer; check broccoli).

title: your choice salad mold
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups water to boiling and dissolve a 3 ounce package of fruit flavored jello.
Chill until slightly thick.
Add undrained crushed pineapple, sour cream and nuts.
Mix well. Congeal.

title: browned rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and brown onion and rice in skillet.
Add consomme and mushrooms with juice.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, covered, in a Pyrex or Corning dish.
If lid does not fit tight, cover with aluminum foil.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans. Chill and serve.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, mayonnaise, minced onion, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: adam's fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add margarine and toss.
Add milk, cheese and seasoning.
Cook over medium heat.
Top with cheese and fresh basil.
Makes 6 side dishes.

title: herbed pork chops
directions: Cook pork chops in oil on high heat (2 minutes each side) until brown.
Reduce heat to medium and continue cooking and turning until cooked through.
Remove to heated dinner plates and keep warm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water (as directed).
Let set until slightly firm.
Put the apple, orange and cranberries, peeling and all, through food grinder or food processor.
Add sugar and let set until Jell-O is ready.
Add this to Jell-O and the chopped nuts.
Set until firm.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and dry milk together.
Add oil to water, being sure yeast is dissolved.
Add dry ingredients to liquid, mixing until it pulls away from sides of bowl or pan.
Knead well and let rise until almost doubled in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll out to desired thickness; cut with biscuit cutter or shape rolls by hand.
Place on greased bread pan and let rise.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
This makes about 8 dozen rolls.
You may make part of dough into loaves.
Bake in loaf pans.
Spread with fresh butter.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Quick fry 1 tortilla at a time in hot oil (375°) to soften.
Spoon tablespoon of chicken mixture onto tortilla. Spread down center and roll. Place seam side down in an oiled baking dish.
When all are filled and rolled, spoon enchilada sauce over top with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with lettuce and tomatoes.
Top with sour cream, guacamole or both.

title: skillet pork chops and rice
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a large skillet.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Core apples and cut into thin wedges.
Stir apples into rice mixture.
Place chops on top of rice mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until rice is tender and chops are heated through.
Spread marmalade evenly over chops.

title: coffee squares
directions: Cream eggs and sugar. Add oil and coffee. Gradually add flour that has been sifted with soda and salt. Pour batter into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan. If this size is not available use 1 (8-inch) square pan and 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple and coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and blend well.
Add crushed pineapple, juice also.
Sift baking powder with flour and add to mixture.
Add one-half of the coconut and the vanilla.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into two buttered cake pans.
Sprinkle the other half cup of coconut over the two layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: salsa
directions: Prepare peppers in a food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until desired consistency.
The longer you cook, the thicker it will become.
When cooked, cold pack it.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in medium baking dish with butter on top at 400° until firm.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place the pork chops into a large baking dish and cover with the chopped onions. Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour over the chops. Bake for about 35 minutes at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
In wok or large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry next 3 ingredients for 2 minutes until tender-crisp.
Remove from wok.
Stir-fry pork, 1/2 at a time, for 3 minutes.
Return pork to wok.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Combine croutons with butter and sprinkle over entire dish.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt butter and add sour cream.
Add dry muffin mix, eggs and onion.
Add drained spinach.
Pour in a cast iron skillet.
Bake like cornbread at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie, 10 to 11 for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Enjoy eating them with milk, coffee, tea or whatever you wish.

title: cottage cheese and jell-o salad
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice.
Add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat and bring to a boil and dissolve Jell-O in it. Set until slightly thickened.
Mix balance of ingredients in bowl and add to thickened Jell-O.
Chill until firm.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into your ice cream freezer.
Fix according to your freezer's instructions.
Yields 1 gallon.
Half this recipe for the Mini-Yum Yum freezer.

title: cherry pie
directions: Heat cherry pie filling with sugar, cinnamon and butter until melted and bubbling.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with lattice strips of pie crust.
Brush strips and crust with milk. Bake in a 400° oven until crust is golden brown (about 25 minutes).

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into batter mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: copper pennies
directions: Place cooked carrots in a large bowl with green pepper, onions; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots mixture and mix.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Let stand about 12 hours before serving.
Drain off part of dressing before serving.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine ingredients in order given; stir after each one is added.
Form into balls and chill until set.

title: rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring milk and salt to simmer.
Stir in rice and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and cook until rice is tender, about 15 minutes. Meanwhile in mixer bowl, beat eggs with sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk. Add 1 cup cooked rice mixture; stir until blended.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel potatoes after they sit and cool.
In a medium mixing bowl, mash peeled potatoes.
Melt butter and pour into mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients; blend well. Pour sweet potato mixture into pie crust.
Bake pie at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice and enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Gel the jello slightly, then beat with soft cream cheese.
Whip Dream Whip and mix with jello and cream cheese.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Put in mold and chill until firm.

title: cheddar cheese with chili dip
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion in the melted shortening.
Add the tomato, green chilies, spices and salt; cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in Cheddar cheese until melted.
Serve as a dip in a chafing dish with any kind of chips or crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crepes marquis
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes.
For each crepe pour 1/4 cup batter into hot lightly greased skillet.
Cook one side only.
Heat oven to 350°. Fry bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Crumble bacon.
Cook onion and green pepper in bacon fat until tender.
Add bacon, mushrooms and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Mix lightly. Fill each crepe with about 1/4 cup cheese mixture; roll.
Place crepes in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: dessert potato cake
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until tender, about 20 minutes. (Do not pierce for tenderness.) Drain. Toss potatoes over low heat to dry completely. Peel immediately. Sieve to equal about 4 cups. Can be prepared one day ahead. Cool completely, cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before using. Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Using electric mixer, beat potatoes, yolks, sugar, peel and cloves until light and fluffy. Spread batter in pan. Bake 40 minutes. Cool, then dust with powdered sugar. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Stir in heavy saucepan the peppers, sugar, salt and mustard. Add flour, vinegar and oleo.
Mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil, boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and put in 1/2 pint jars and seal.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup and melt cheese in soup.
Add gelatin which has been softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let cool and add other ingredients.
Pour in mold and refrigerate until it is firm.

title: cleo's dessert
directions: Mix ice cream, milk and pudding mix.
Save part of cracker mixture, press remainder in bottom of pan.
Pour ice cream mixture on top.
Cover with whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with saved cracker mixture.
Put in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine bran, oats and milk.
Set aside.
Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and spices separately. Blend pumpkin with egg whites, oil and raisins. Add to bran.
Add dry ingredients and stir until moist.
Spray 12 muffin tins with Pam.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.

title: great potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: slumgullion
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and place in large greased baking dish. Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain and add to spaghetti.
Add tomatoes and cheese; mix well.
Top with bread crumbs and few dots of butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello and fruit squares
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl until dissolved. Mix cold juice and ice to make 1 1/2 cups. Stir into gelatin. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened. Remove 1 1/2 cups gelatin; stir in fruit. Stir 1/2 Cool Whip into remaining gelatin with wire whisk until blended.

Pour into 8-inch square dish. Refrigerate 10 minutes until set but not firm. Carefully spoon fruited gelatin over creamy layer in dish. Refrigerate 3 hours. Cut into squares. Put a spoonful of Cool Whip on top of Jell-O.

title: inez's broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave or boil broccoli just to wilt.
Combine eggs and milk; combine soup and mayonnaise.
Pour first into second and mix. Stir in cheese and broccoli.
Coat a casserole with nonstick spray and pour in mixture.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, then add Cool Whip. Stir well and chill.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 teaspoon of cold water.
Stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add shrimp and green peppers.
Simmer and cover until done.

title: e-z cake
directions: Grease and flour pan (9 x 13). Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with E-Z Frosting.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork until smooth, adding milk to soften.
Add sour cream.
Peel cucumbers and remove pulpy seeds. Grate into cream mixture.
Add pinch of dill and shake of garlic salt.
Leave in refrigerator for several hours.
Enjoy with your favorite potato chips or crackers.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: With just enough water to cover vegetables, bring to a boil and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Fold in cooked vegetables; mix well.

title: mocha(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix cocoa and coffee in pot or pitcher.
Pour in boiling water and stir.
Serve hot and topped with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cheese in milk.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Sprinkle top with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish or dish over candle warmer with chips or small pieces of toast.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with the sugar.
Add the milk, salt and vanilla. Sprinkle top of pie with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then drop oven to 350° for 30 minutes or when dinner knife is inserted in pie and comes out clean.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage (235°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat mixture with a wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased wax paper.
Let stand until candy is firm.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour and seasoning.
Dredge mixture thoroughly into both sides of steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Place fryer over medium heat and add shortening.
Brown meat well on both sides. Mix vegetables and place over meat.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken remaining sauce for gravy.
Serves 6.

title: never fail yeast bread
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.

title: blondies
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and let set.
Cut and enjoy!

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Place mix in greased baking dish.
Top with nuts and bake at 350° until hot. Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick foil or with regular foil; coat with nonstick spray.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients to a consistent bread dough and roll out in sections.
Sprinkle each section with flour or corn meal.
With each ball or section about 1/4-inch thick, punch hole into center and fry, one at a time in 2 to 3-inches of shortening at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in bowl.
Melt margarine or butter.
Pour butter into baking dish.
Pour batter over butter.
Pour fruit on top of batter. Bake until brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together Veg-All, cheese, mayonnaise and cooked onion. Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Spread crackers over Veg-All mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: I add 1 cup grated sharp New York cheese and 1 tablespoon onion flakes with squash.
I also add topping of bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and butter flavored cooking spray.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Brown onion in margarine until tender; add curry.
Combine with remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Let simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: sunshine shakes(for kids)
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: breakfast schnitzel
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Dip in milk, then egg.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with salt.
Fry in 1/2-inch deep shortening in skillet for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Transfer to a large bowl; add the next 10 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add first five ingredients together.
Cook sauce to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spread sauce on bottom of pan. Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, then sauce. Repeat, but end with sauce!
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Add rest of the ingredients except ice cream.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 the mixture on 2 loaf cake pans.
Slice ice cream 1-inch thick.
Place on top of this mixture.
Press rest of the mixture on top of the ice cream.
Freeze.
Great for company or showers!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with fresh fruit.

title: devil by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directions on box in a 9 x 13 pan. When cool, cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Soak cake cubes in Kahlua overnight. Make mousse. Layer in large bowl (2 to 3 layers) cake, mousse, Cool Whip and candy (repeat), ending with Cool Whip and candy. Chill overnight. Keeps well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except oats, flour and raisins.
After mixing, then stir in oats, flour and raisins. Drop dough by rounded teaspoons about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.
Contains 110 calories per cookie.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder; set aside. Cream shortening; gradually add sugar and unbeaten eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Mix in the oatmeal, vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
The dough will be thick.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Grease casserole and pour in the pork and beans,
Dice onion and add to pork and beans.
Now add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cut the bacon into 1 inch pieces and place on top of beans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: deitrich's potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken stock, butter, sour
cream, heavy cream, milk, basil and garlic.
Heat until sauce thickens slightly.
Peel potatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.
Place potatoes in dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt together.
Cook on Full power for 20 to 22 minutes in microwave.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually pour mixture into egg whites while beating. Beat mixture until it loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts and drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread, but do not allow to rise.
(You may use frozen sweet dough.)
Break or cut dough into 9 equal parts and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter, then add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon.
Blend well and pour over bread.
Break or cut second loaf into same number of parts and place over first bread. Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°. When you take them out of the oven, turn them over on a cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Makes 18 rolls.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Slice rolls of cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices.
Place one roll of slices in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and press together to cover bottom.
Spoon on cream cheese mixture.
Crumble up remaining slices of cookie dough and place evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden and center is lightly firm.
Remove from oven.
Let cool, then refrigerate.
Slice when completely cool.

title: chicken broccoli and stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place in small bowl and add ginger, garlic	powder and 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Mix and set aside.	Chop broccoli and carrots.
In hot wok or skillet stir-fry chicken in oil until brown.
Add vegetables and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add water mixed with	remaining
soy	sauce and cornstarch.
Cover and cook 5 to 8
minutes
or
until	carrots
are semi tender. Serve over rice.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
With floured hands, spread cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool crust.
Prepare instant pudding as label directs but use 1 1/4 cups milk and add almond extract.
Spread pudding on top of crust, then slice fruit and arrange on top of pudding.
Serve immediately.
If not serving immediately, cover and refrigerate.
This dessert is not good on the day you make it.

title: cheesy hash brown bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until lightly brown and bubbly. This can be made ahead and chilled in refrigerator until ready to use.
Takes about an additional 15 minutes baking time.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Lightly brown sausage and drain.
No need to cook until done. This will eliminate some of the grease.
Then mix the remaining ingredients with the sausage and form into 1-inch balls.
They can be frozen at this point, if desired.
Place in the oven frozen and bake for 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet at 400°.

title: s e x
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine, place in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Add flour and pecans; mix.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool

title: creamed california vegetables
directions: Put veggies in casserole with cream soup, cheese and 1/2 can onions, then mix together.
Top with rest of can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot.

title: italian vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tomato sauce, basil, oregano and garlic.
Spray an 8 x 5-inch baking dish.
Arrange vegetables in layers in baking dish as follows:
zucchini, onion, tomato, tomato sauce, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Repeat twice more. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, covered.
Let cool a few minutes before serving.
Serves 2 as main dish or 4 as side dish.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Stir together sour cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze in cupcake liners.
Put in muffin tins to hold shape.
Remove from liners and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 9.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make a loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley (or dill weed), onion and tabasco.
Stir in tuna.
Place in oiled mold.
Chill 3 hours. Unmold and decorate with sliced olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all cake ingredients, beat smooth and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crumble crackers and wafers together.
Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Add coconut, raisins, chopped pecans and cherries.
Mix thoroughly (mixes best by hand).
Add milk and reserved cherry juice.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Press into lightly oiled tube pan or 3 foil lined loaf pans. Allow to set in refrigerator several hours.
Turn out and wrap well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
May also be frozen.

title: yarmouth straws
directions: Before adding the water to pastry mix, add the grated cheese and mustard.
Divide the pastry in half; roll out one half into a rectangle fairly thin.
Place on baking tray; brush with beaten egg.
Place kipper fillets on pastry.
Roll out another rectangle a little bigger than the lower rectangle.
Place on top of fillets; press down all sides.
Brush over with beaten egg; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, trim off edges and cut into neat, bite size strips.
Serve on plate with parsley garnish. Serves approximately 12 to 15.

title: cinnamon strip snacks
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Set aside. Lightly brown tortillas; cut into strips.
Roll in sugar mixture while still hot.
Serve while still warm.

title: white peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and milk to the soft ball stage.
(To test, use candy thermometer or drop 1/2 teaspoon of the hot mixture in cold water and if it forms a ball or circle, it is ready.)
Stir the peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme into the hot mixture and immediately pour it into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put dry ingredients in a bowl.
Work shortening in until size of corn meal.
Put egg and vinegar in cup.
Beat until mixed together.
Add water to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Mix with shortening and dry ingredients until stiff dough forms.
Roll out on floured board.

title: zesty zucchini bake
directions: Saute onions
and
garlic in oil in skillet or saucepan until lightly
browned
and tender.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and vinegar.
Bring
to
a
boil
and
simmer
for
minute. Arrange zucchini
slices
in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with tomato and onion mixture.	Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 1
hour or until zucchini is tender.
Makes 10 cups or 8 to 10 servings.

title: n.c. style barbecue sauce
directions: Heat first five ingredients in saucepan until hot.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to rapid boil, then simmer slowly for 1 hour.

title: fresh squeezed lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and cold water; mix well and chill.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon or lime slices and/or fresh mint sprigs.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine butter, eggs, sugar and bananas to a creamy mixture. Slowly add in flour and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil, slowly stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Do not stir!
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat and stir in 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together with warm water.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Heat bread pan hot with Crisco oil.
Pour in pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Combine green beans, corn, green peas, celery and onion in large bowl; mix well.
Add dressing; mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain before serving.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Turn vegetables into saucepan.
Add onions, flour, salad herbs, salt and pepper.
Mix until vegetables are coated with the flour.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: wonton soup
directions: Boil rib bones or neck bones.
Chill; skim fat.
Spoon pork hamburger into wonton wrapper.
Drop it in boiling soup.
Serve green onions and sprinkle with wontons.

title: toffee crescent bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into ungreased jelly roll pan. Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil in small sauce pan. Boil for a full minute. Drizzle over rolls. Sprinkle pecans over all. Bake 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips. Cool and cut.

title: feather rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1-1/4 c. warm water.
Mix butter, salt, egg and milk in lrg. bowl and beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down again and make into rolls.
Cover and let rise 30 min.
Bake at 400° for 15-20 min.

title: great-grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until light brown.

title: broccoli ham and cheese ring
directions: Mix mustard, lemon juice and sour cream in a bowl.
Add chopped onion, parsley, ham and broccoli.
Add grated cheese. Arrange the crescent rolls in a circle with points out like a star and the center overlapping.
Place mixture in center and fold the ends of the rolls into the middle.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green fruit punch
directions: Mix in large container and put in pint plastic freezer containers and put in freezer.
Chop punch and mix with ginger ale.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Place chicken in
pan.	Spread	with mayonnaise.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: easy mushroom dish
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms.
Set aside.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add mushrooms along with lemon juice and garlic.
Saute 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in chopped parsley, salt, pepper and oregano leaves.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: peach crumble
directions: Arrange slices in shallow greased baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: indian jumanas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla until fluffy; stir in sour cream.
Blend together dry ingredients; stir into butter mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in butter.
Stir in mushrooms, parsley and seasonings.
Sprinkle over cubes.
Add eggs and bouillon.
Mix. Put in slow cooker and cover.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low and continue to cook for 1 to 2 more hours.

title: daisy bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, yeast, margarine, sugar and water.
Beat. Add remaining flour.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Let rest 15 to 20 minutes.
Shape into daisy bread.
Refrigerate 2 to 48 hours. Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: saucy tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In medium skillet, heat oil and cook onion and green pepper until tender. Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine noodles, sauce and tuna. Bake, covered, 30 minutes or until heated through. Top with cheese.
Let stand, covered, until cheese is melted.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: diet bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
In saucepan warm milk; stir in sugar and shortening.
Add yeast and mix well.
Work in flour. Shape in a ball and place in a greased bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again, about greased 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Remove stems and seeds from peppers.
Stuff with finely grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Make dough with Cheddar, Bisquick and sausage (works best if you use your hands to make dough stick together).
Pinch dough to wrap each stuffed pepper.
Roll in the Shake 'n Bake and place on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for a few hours.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 servings.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk.
Add milk last.
Mix well. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat cider vinegar and sugar to boil until sugar is
dissolved.
Cool and stir in vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 weeks.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Open all cans of fruit, drain off juice, using strainer.
Cut sliced peaches and mandarin oranges.
Mix together in mixing bowl all fruits.
Stir in lemon juice, condensed milk and Cool Whip. Mix well together.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla extract; mix thoroughly.
Press two-thirds of dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves; crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: rice pilaf norcian
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add finely broken vermicelli and cook until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice. Dissolve chicken seasoned stock base in boiling water and pour over rice and vermicelli.
Stir in instant minced onion.
Cover and steam for 25 minutes or until all stock is absorbed.
Fluff with fork.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: appetizer sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with egg rolls or cocktail franks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, broth and vegetables and pour over chicken.
Mix margarine (room temperature or melted), flour, milk and pepper and pour on top (do not mix in).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Blend 2 eggs, cake mix and butter together with a fork and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend together 3 remaining eggs and cream cheese, then add powdered sugar and beat.
Pour into cake pan and save a little powdered sugar to sprinkle over cake when done. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "crabby" alfredo(cheap, quick and easy)
directions: Boil noodles according to directions.
Prepare alfredo sauce according to directions on package.
Heat imitation crab meat in microwave until very warm.
Mix crabby meat with alfredo sauce. Serve over fettucine noodles.
Add a tossed salad and you have a wonderful meal!

title: broccoli, cheese and rice
directions: Put oil in skillet and saute broccoli, onion and celery. Add Cheez Whiz to cooked rice. Add to broccoli, onion and celery mixture; stir well. Add chicken soup and chicken bouillon that has been dissolved in small amount of hot water. Mix all very well. Add milk. Stir and pour into a 9 x 13 greased casserole. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place basil, Parmesan and garlic in food processor until coarsely ground.
Gradually add olive oil until well blended.
Add walnuts; process until blended.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.

title: breakfast pastry
directions: Preheat your oven to 400°. Roll out puff pastry sheets. Softly scramble 7 eggs and place in center of pastry. Wilt spinach and layer on top of eggs. Continue with ham and then shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Top with second sheet of puff pastry. Seal edges with an egg wash and brush top with egg wash. Cook until golden brown on sheet pan.

title: texas barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in Dutch oven with water.
Add celery, carrot, onion, parsley, bouillon granules and pepper; bring to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken pieces; place in
a 2-quart casserole.
Strain broth; skim off fat.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the broth for sauce (cover and refrigerate remaining broth for another use).

title: raggedy ann cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter thoroughly.
Add eggs.
Sift and measure flour; add soda and mix.
Add vanilla, raisins and corn flakes.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 315°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil margarine, brown sugar, Karo syrup slowly for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda and salt.
Mix in popcorn and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in finely chopped beef, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into ovenproof dish. Crisp pecans with butter and sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with "nutty-style" crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and make into a ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Put in saucer and cool.
Cream margarine and Crisco 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Add sugar gradually and beat 4 minutes.
Add cooled paste (remove the skin).
Beat 4 minutes. Add vanilla and blend.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons. Add sugar and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: pizza planks
directions: Cut the French bread in half lengthwise.
Remove some of the soft bread to make a slightly hollowed loaf.
Place each half on a plate, cut sides up.
Spoon spaghetti sauce evenly over both halves.
Arrange pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese evenly over the tops.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High for another 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: ginger grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken several hours.
Thread boneless chicken chunks on kabobs with vegetables for delicious kabobs.
Grill for best flavor.
Marinate chicken parts for great grilled treat. (Less expensive than boneless cuts!)

title: fluff
directions: Heat pineapple.
When warm, stir in jello until dissolved. Put aside to cool, then add cottage cheese.
Mix evenly, then add Cool Whip.
Mix again.
Place in refrigerator until thick.
Serve for dessert or may be served on bed of lettuce as an appetizer.

title: soda cracker cookie(taste like heath bar)
directions: Spread crackers on a greased cookie sheet to cover area.
Boil sugar and oil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes at 400°.

title: russian tea
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Quarter, do not peel, and boil slowly without adding water.
Cook until peelings come off easily.
Stir often.

title: white potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into the mashed potatoes and put in an unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top, if desired, and bake slightly longer to melt.

title: garden club chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put into 2-quart baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken and then sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients together and add fruit. Stir lightly so that most of the fruit stays on top. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grape sunshine
directions: Strain cooked grapes through colander.
Measure the juice and fine pulp together.
Add 1 cup sugar to each cup of grape juice pulp.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars, leaving headspace of 1/2-inch.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours undisturbed.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze.
May cover with paraffin wax and store on shelf.

title: boxed au gratin potatoes - not
directions: Scrub potatoes well; do not peel.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices. Mix soup with 1 teaspoon paprika in bowl; set aside.
Start layering in casserole dish, layer of potatoes; spread some soup mixture on top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Keep repeating until finished; top with bread crumbs to cover.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: pasta and shrimp salad
directions: Add shrimp to boiling water.
Cover, turn off heat and simmer 5 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp. Cook vermicelli according to package directions, rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine shrimp and vermicelli.
Add celery, olives, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour over pasta mixture and toss. Cover and chill.
Yields 8 servings.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Stir together corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. In a separate bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in milk and cooking oil.
Add liquid to dry mixture.
Stir in corn, peppers, cheese and onions.
Pour in greased pan and cook until done.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crusts, and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill before serving. Refrigerate.

title: cherry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box.
Mix in all ingredients. Place in refrigerator and allow to congeal.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients until blended well.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pizza style
directions: Brown
ground
beef,
onion, salt and black
pepper
in shortening.
Add
tomato
soup
and
cook together
about	15 minutes, until thickened.
Cook macaroni according	to
directions and drain well.
Beat together milk and egg and
add
to macaroni. Spread macaroni mixture on greased cookie	sheet or sheet cake pan.
Cover macaroni with tomato beef mixture.
Top with
cheese. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for
minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: s-que-wi(cabbage)
directions: Chop cabbage; wilt in hot grease (small amount).
Add half of a green pepper, chopped.
Cook until cabbage turns red.
Serve with cornbread.

title: yummy rice pudding
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, bring 3 cups of water to a boil. Add rice to boiling water.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook over very low heat about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat and strain the water off the rice in a strainer.
Return rice to saucepan and add the remaining ingredients.

title: lentil tex mix
directions: Wash the lentils and cook in salted water, bringing to a boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Drain and save water.
Add butter to lentils and mash.
Add liquid back to lentils to get a smooth consistency.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly grease 9-10 inch pie pan. Sprinkle bacon or ham, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender-blend on high speed. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted into center comes out clean; 50-55 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves:

title: chocolate chip meringues
directions: Before beginning, grease cookie sheets and preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto sheets.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off and leave in for 2 hours or overnight.
(Overnight not recommended during periods of high humidity.)

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions.
Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple together.
Pour into cake pan.
Place stick of butter into dough and bake for 50 minutes.
Spoon out of pan to serve.

title: mediterranean dip(eggplant)
directions: Wash eggplant.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In 1/2 cup olive oil, saute eggplant until tender. Drain.
Place eggplant, onion, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil and salt in blender and blend on high speed until smooth. Serve with raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chili(makes a lot.)
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon. Leave a little grease. Place everything in stockpot. Mix well. Cook on low heat a few hours. The longer it cooks-the better it tastes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Stir well and dredge potatoes in this mixture. Lay potatoes in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole, dotting each layer with butter. Bake at 400° for an hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix and set aside the oats, pecans and peanut butter.
Put remaining ingredients in skillet.
Bring to rolling boil and let boil 1 minute.
(I use iron skillet so it might take longer in another skillet.)
Stir in first mixture and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Drop teaspoonful on waxed paper and let set.
I usually add extra oats.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix together the beans, meat, onion and bacon.
Stir together the brown sugar, vinegar, catsup and mustard.
Add this to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot pie
directions: Drain juice off apricots.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups. Add jello and pudding and cook until it boils.
Chill.
Cut up the apricots (save 3 for top).
Whip up Dream Whip; fold into pudding mixture.
Chill for 2 hours in a graham cracker crust.

title: stirred rice pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan bring milk to boiling.
Stir in uncooked rice and raisins.
Cover.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 40 minutes or until most of the milk is absorbed.
(Mixture may appear curdled.) Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli, including stalks, into cubes.
Add olives, onion and chopped eggs.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Toss with broccoli spears.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spray dish with no stick spray.
Layer bottom of dish with chips.
Place chicken (deboned) on
top of chips.
Smooth first
4 ingredients over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into thirty 1-inch balls. Place in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cook, uncovered, in a 400° oven, until done, 15 to 18 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in this order.
Spread with salad dressing.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in sherry for 1 hour.
Drain and discard sherry. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda twice.
Set aside.
Cream butter, lemon rind and sugar together.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Fold in fruits alternately with flour mixture.
Place mixture into a greased and lined 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cooked.
Cool on wire rack.
Ice, if desired, with icing of your choice.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: dutch meat loaf dinner
directions: In mixing bowl, combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1 cup tomato sauce with water, egg, salt, vinegar and mustard.
Shape into round loaf and put in center of roasting pan.
This allows room for vegetables around loaf.
Add carrots and potatoes, pour tomatoes over vegetables around loaf.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or longer, until done.
Baste several times during cooking.

title: apple streusel
directions: Cut oleo into flour using a pastry cutter.
Add yolks, vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Divide into 3 pieces.
Roll on floured board.
Sprinkle each with filling.
Roll and place on ungreased pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
You can use canned pie filling.

title: quick steak
directions: Place steak in large square of aluminum foil.
Season and sprinkle soup mix over steak.
Bake at 350° to desired doneness. Yields 5 servings.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients
together.
Add
to eggs, milk and oil. Stir only until bubbly.
"Don't stir after."

title: whoopie cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove.
Put frosting on 1 cookie and top with another to make a cream-filled style cookie.

title: luscious strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and chopped nuts.
Pour half the mixture into an oiled 9-inch square pan.
Chill slightly.
Fold sour cream into remaining gelatin mixture and pour into the pan of partially set gelatin.
Chill until firmly set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: *Two whole eggs may be used and increase flour to 2 tablespoons.

title: jennifer's baked beans
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Drizzle with dark molasses.
Bake for about 2 hours at 350°.
Stir.
Will thicken after it cools for about 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water.
Melt butter in pan and saute chopped onion, bell pepper and pimento.
Add chicken, soup, salt and pepper.
Drain and add spaghetti.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Do not preheat oven.
In large pot, boil macaroni and onions for 10 minutes.
Mix hash and half of cheese (break up cheese) in bowl.
Drain macaroni and onions; add hash and cheese.
Mix thoroughly, while adding half cup of milk slowly.
Pour into greased baking pan; add rest of milk.
Put rest of cheese on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Set oven at 325°.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and milk.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Stir sugar over apples.
Pour batter over butter.
Add apples on top.
Bake at 350° until done, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat well-greased heavy 8 or 10-inch skillet and cover lightly with corn meal.
Stir sugar into corn meal.
Stir beaten egg and vegetable oil into milk.
Mix all ingredients; pour into skillet and bake in 425° oven, preheated, 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: glenda's squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine with stuffing mix; place half in dish.
Mix squash, onion, soup and sour cream.
Add shredded carrot for color.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine cheese, margarine, mayonnaise and seasoned salt; heat. Break into small pieces and add seafood chunks.
Split muffins and lay on a cookie sheet.
Spread mixture on halves.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly. Cut into quarters and serve warm.

title: million dollar banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk (blend on low with mixer).
Add Eagle Brand. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and mix; wafers, bananas and mix, etc.
Top with extra wafers, if desired.
Fits a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ranch beef loaf
directions: Put bread
crumbs
in
a
large bowl and pour milk over them. Stir in ground beef, salt, pepper, grated carrot, onion and beaten eggs.
Lightly shape the meat loaf mixture into an oval loaf. Put in a shallow pan; set aside.
Mix the ketchup, brown sugar and
mustard and spread over the top of the loaf. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, stir together the corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in freezer or coldest part of refrigerator until firm.
Cut cereal mixture into twelve 3-inch squares.
Sandwich each slice of the ice cream between 2 squares.
Freeze until firm.
Cut each large sandwich in half and wrap individually in foil.
Store in freezer until needed.
Yields 12 sandwiches.

title: snow pudding
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and sugar; stir.
Add strained lemon juice.
Chill until it begins to harden.
Beat egg white to a stiff froth.
Add to slightly hardened mix.
Beat until spongy.
Chill until hard.

title: jane's lasagna
directions: Brown beef and cook onion, garlic and oregano.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Alternate noodles, cottage cheese, sauce and grated Mozzarella cheese in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nannie's chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl add all ingredients above and mix for 10 minutes. Pour in 2 or 3, 9 inch cake pans and cook at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into long rolls.
Place on platter and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 375° until done.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Add hot water to gelatin.
Heat tomato soup.
In a blender, add hot soup, gelatin, cream cheese, mayonnaise and basil.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into bowl and add celery, onion and shrimp. Gently mix.
Fill 6 cup mold and chill until firm.

title: cream sauce for baked potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients together.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onion and mushrooms in oil.
Spoon into 2-quart dish.
Stir in broccoli, soup and sour cream.
Pour over casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken breasts diane(yields 4 servings)
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Transfer to warm platter.

title: lisa's best tasting bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup of cereal, boiling water and oil; set aside. Combine flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and remaining cereal.
Add eggs and milk to dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in cereal and oil mixture.
Add raisins, if desired.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix together the sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: roasted beef tenderloin
directions: Combine butter and seasonings; mix well.
Place tenderloin on rack in roasting pan.
Brush with butter mixture.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes to 45 minutes or until thermometer reaches 140° for rare, 150° for medium rare or 160° for medium.
Serve with sour cream and prepared horseradish.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken with salt, pepper and 1/2 onion.
Debone chicken. Saute with other 1/2 of onion.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup, 8 ounces of sour cream, green chillies and 8 ounces Monterey Jack cheese.
Put mixture in flour tortillas.
Roll up each.
Put in pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix other can of cream of mushroom soup, rest of cheese and rest of sour cream together. Pour over enchiladas.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onions*.
Drain some of juice from all the beans and save to add if needed during baking.
Mix all ingredients together and bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. This is a great dish for a potluck.

title: ginger baby carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes, until tender.

title: eggnog
directions: In large saucepan, beat together eggs and sugar.
Stir in 2 cups milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining 2 cup milk and vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, several hours.
Just before serving, stir in cinnamon stick and ground nutmeg.

title: macadamia nut crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cookie crumbs and 6 tablespoons butter.
Press into bottom of an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan. Place nuts in a single layer over crust. Combine 1 cup brown sugar with 1 1/2 cups butter.
Heat over medium flame until surface boils.
Pour
over nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light brown. Remove and cool on rack.

title: rice custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Set in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until done.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Core bell peppers.
Mix ground beef, rice, Ro-Tel tomatoes, salt, pepper and garlic together.
Put mixture in bell peppers, pour tomato soup and water over peppers and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Beat the ham, cayenne, butter and 2 of the eggs into the potatoes. Let the mixture cool slightly and shape it like croquettes. Roll in the bread crumbs. Dip in beaten egg and again in crumbs. Put in the frying basket and plunge into boiling fat. Cook 2 minutes. Drain and serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: quick pear crumble
directions: Place 8 pear halves, cut-side up, in broiler-proof pan. Combine remaining ingredients.
Crumble over pears.
Broil 6-inches from heat for about 3 minutes, until browned.

title: easy-quick spaghetti for 2
directions: Brown beef with onions; drain off fat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add the spaghetti.
Mix well.
Turn into small casserole.
Top with Cheddar.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Double for 4 etc.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and shortening; mix. Add vanilla and applesauce; mix again.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Bake in muffin cups at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: squash spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, squash, applesauce and orange juice.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Gradually add to squash mixture, blending well.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting or sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Pour all ingredients into electric blender and blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into a buttered pie plate and let set for 5 minutes.
Top with nutmeg.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: In large mixing bowl, put in all ingredients.
Mix well; pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Crab Delight and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.

title: lemon cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar
and
cream
cheese
until	fluffy. Beat in lemon
juice,
vanilla,	lemon extract, orange extract and salt.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition. Add flour; beat until
smooth.	Pour
batter
into greased and floured Bundt pan.	Bake at
325° for 90 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes. Remove from
pan
and
cool
completely.
Pour glaze over cake and serve.

title: eight layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9-inch glass pie pan, starting with bean dip on bottom and ending with olives on top.
Serve with Fritos for dipping.

title: scallops nantucket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place scallops in large ovenproof casserole.
Drizzle each portion with 1 tablespoon butter, 2 tablespoons vermouth and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until scallops are almost firm. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted golden brown.
Serve with a side of pasta and a fresh green salad.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil vegetables until tender but not thoroughly cooked.
In a casserole dish, mix vegetables, mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: polish sausage crock-pot stew
directions: Combine soup, sugar and sauerkraut.
Stir in sausage, potatoes and onion.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours (or high 4 hours) in crock-pot cooker.
When ready to serve, sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: key west chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter and flour and stir 2 minutes over medium heat.
Gradually add half and half, stirring another 2 minutes. Set aside.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Drain apricots, reserving syrup. Press apricots through sieve or puree in blender. Add enough reserved syrup to make 1 cup; set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter, add flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add potatoes and simmer 7 minutes.
Pour into shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until tender, about 35 minutes.
If desired, may be sprinkled with cheese before baking.

title: chicken coating mix
directions: Mix all ingredients is a bowl.
Coat chicken.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Chop onions and bell pepper.
Mix with corn and let set for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Add 2 tomatoes, cut up. Add enough mayonnaise to mix and hold together.

title: creamy mushroom baked potatoes
directions: You will need a 2-quart square Pyrex baking dish.

title: manicotti with three cheeses
directions: Cook manicotti in a large pot of boiling water according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again.

title: abigail adams' champagne punch
directions: Tea is an unusual addition to this refreshing punch popular for gatherings in the 1700's.

title: brandy apple cake
directions: Combine and mix first 3 ingredients and let stand for 1 hour. Then add the remaining by hand.
Bake one hour at 350° in greased and floured loaf pans or 1 large tube pan.
(Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.)
Can be wrapped and frozen for later use.

title: parsons wafers
directions: Mix and chill dough of butter, cream and flour 1 hour. Roll out onto a sugared board 1/8-inch thick. Turn dough over in sugar to coat both sides. Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles. Prick tops with fork. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 7 to 9 minutes at 375°, until puffy and light gold in color. Cool.

title: pork chop parmesan
directions: Combine flour, garlic, paprika, pepper and parsley in plastic bag.
Dredge pork chops.
Melt margarine.
Add oil.
Brown chops on both sides.
Place chops in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine mushroom soup and pan drippings.
Spoon over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mock filet mignon patties
directions: Place bacon on a bacon rack in a 12x8x2 inch baking dish; cover with paper toweling.
Microwave at High for 5 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes or until bacon is done; crumble bacon, set aside.
Combine ground beef and next 5 ingredients, mixing well; shape into 8 patties about 1/4 inch thick.
Place one-fourth of bacon on center of each of 4 patties, and press edges to seal.
Place patties in a 12x8x2 inch baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper, and microwave at High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Turn patties over; cover and microwave 1 1/2 to 3 additional minutes or until desired degree of doneness. Remove patties to serving platter; cover and let stand.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from baking dish; add remaining ingredients to dish.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap, and microwave at High for 8-10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Spoon vegetables over
patties.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring 2 cups milk and rice to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer over low heat until rice is tender, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in margarine.
In a bowl, combine remaining 2 cups milk, beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir rice mixture into egg mixture.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Remove from oven and stir.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Return to oven; bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Use the knife test to check for doneness.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Mix the lemon juice, soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese over soup.
Melt butter; mix with bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bread crumbs are browned.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2 eggs well and spread in 13 x 9-inch greased
cake
pan.
Then
in
another
bowl, mix 1 box powdered sugar,
eggs
and
cream
cheese.
Mix with beater until creamy.
Pour
over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine. Remove from heat. Fold in marshmallows. Spread nuts on a waxed paper covered cookie sheet. Cover with marshmallow mixture and spread. Roll up like a jelly roll. Refrigerate until solid. Slice and serve.

title: cold stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut stem ends off tomatoes.
Discard seeds and scoop out pulp. Sprinkle inside with salt; turn upside down on paper towel for 10 minutes or so.
Chop pulp and press out as much liquid as possible.
Combine pulp, drained peas and remaining ingredients. Dry insides of tomatoes; stuff with mixture.
Chill until serving time.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Combine butter and powdered sugar; beat well until creamy. Blend in the flour and cardamon.
Add coconut, stirring until dough does not stick to your hands.
Roll out on wax paper about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into pieces with a cookie cutter.
Bake on wax-papered cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until golden brown at 300°.
Makes 40 pieces.

title: plum pudding
directions: Cook raisins and currants until soft and drain.
Mix raisins, currants and lard with 1 cup boiling water; add your spices, and sugar.
Dissolve soda in a little hot water.
Add flour.
Place in greased steamer and steam 3 hours.
Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: pear, cheese and almond salad
directions: Place halves of pears on lettuce leaves.
Fill hollow and heap in a pyramid cream cheese and almonds which have been mixed with mayonnaise. Top with unsweetened whipped cream (add 1/4 teaspoon almond extract).
Sprinkle over top with chopped nuts.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese-ham ball
directions: Chop ham and beef in processor.
(Put some aside to roll ball in.)
Mix cream cheese, onions and the rest of the meat together into a ball. Roll it in the meat that was set aside.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Shape into small balls.
Lay on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mary's orange blossom muffins
directions: Beat eggs,
sugar,
orange juice, salad oil and biscuit mix vigorously	for 30 seconds.
Stir in marmalade and pecans. Line muffin pans with paper
baking
cups
and
fill
2/3 with batter. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cake brownies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients and pour over the next 5 ingredients. Mix well. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Pour into a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet. Mixture will be thin. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Frost with peanut butter frosting.

title: sardine appetizer
directions: Mash sardines with fork.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Mound on serving dish with black olive garnishes.
Serve on toasted rounds or onion or other crackers.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients including sugar (except dry ingredients) and let
soak
for 1 hour.	Then add to dry mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until done.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Melt wax and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Stir until melted.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes. Stir together.
Drop mixture on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan. Drain grease, then add the remaining ingredients. Add 4 to 5 tomato paste cans of water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent from sticking.

title: mom frazier's fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball; let cool then beat.
Add nuts if desired.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Do not cook macaroni.
Just mix all ingredients together.
In buttered casserole, soak all ingredients for at least 4 hours before baking.
(Can leave in refrigerator overnight.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't cover.

title: fudge quickies
directions: In saucepan, combine the first four ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Can add more milk for moisture to keep from being sticky.
Cool and eat.
Yummy.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Blanche, cool and chop cauliflower, broccoli and asparagus. Chop and add tomatoes, squash, mushrooms, peas and carrots to cooled vegetables.
In a skillet, add 1 tablespoon butter per serving and chopped mixed veggies.
Stir and add crushed garlic. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add pasta and mix well.
Add heavy cream.
Stir.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese per serving on top.
Stir.
Remove from skillet and place in serving dishes. Garnish with pine nuts and watercress.

title: mexican quiche on chips
directions: Mix eggs in sauce.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch pan half the cheeses, all the sauce, then rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.
Serve on tortilla chips.

title: coconut fluff cake
directions: In bowl, stir together gelatin and 2 c. boiling water, 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 c. water, cover and chill 25 minutes.
Stir in 1 container whipped topping.
Folded in blueberries 1 c. coconut and cake pieces, spoon into plastic wrap lined 10 inch tube pan. Shill 2 hours or until set.
Remove cake from pan; discard plastic wrap.
Frost cake with remaining whipped topping.
Coat with remaining coconut.
Garnish with berries.

title: batinjan
directions: Trim and wash meat then place in medium saucepan and cover with boiling water

(meat must be completely covered). Boil for 5 minutes with lid uncovered, drain meat and discard water. Slice the egg plant about 1/2 inch thick and fry using 2 tablespoons of oil until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper and set aside. In a medium saucepan place 1 tablespoon of oil. Place on medium heat and fry onions and garlic until brown. Add meat and fry together for 1-2 minutes. Pour boiling water, cover pan and boil for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Now add chopped tomatoes, tomato puree, lemon juice, salt and garam masala.
Add the egg plant to the pan and boil for 15 minutes on medium heat, then stir gently, simmer for a further 15 minutes. Serve with hot rice, salad or bread. Freezes well.

title: pasta and rice
directions: Cook ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Drain off fat.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix all together in a casserole dish.
Add tomato soup and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour..

title: fresh strawberry pie(microwave)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook Jell-O, sugar, cornstarch and water in microwave on High power for 2 minutes.
Continue cooking until cloudy mixture boils and becomes clear, stirring after each minute.
Cool.
Arrange sliced berries in pie shell. Pour jell-O mixture over berries.
Refrigerate until mixture sets, about 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip topping.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinate
meat, using the garlic, cumin, oregano, salt, orange juice,
vinegar
and
hot
sauce
for 15 minutes.
In a Dutch oven,
saute
onion, bell pepper and meat for 5 minutes; set aside.
Place
some
olive
oil
(or oil) in a skillet and heat. Quickly
cook
tortilla and form into a taco.
Place on paper towels
to drain.
Don't overcook and make it too crisp. Ladle meat into shells and garnish with cheese and lettuce.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Melt margarine, add onion and saute.
Add remaining ingredients, except ham.
Place ham in a casserole and add sauce. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: home canned tomato soup
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients and put through food mill.
Add the remaining 5 ingredients.
Put in cans and process.

title: baked chicken
directions: Use boneless, skinless chicken breast.
Mix ingredients together and spread over chicken in a large baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until the chicken is done, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: *Add 1/2 cup chopped onions if potatoes are plain type.

title: lennie's tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add soup; put soda in can and add a small amount of water.
Stir, then put in cake.
Add spices and baking powder to flour and sift into cake.
Add raisins and nuts dropped in flour.
Bake in large pan in slow oven (325°) for about 40 minutes or until done.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine Dates and 1 tablespoon of Flour.
Add Water; simmer 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in Vanilla.
Combine Brown Sugar with 1 cup of Flour, Baking Soda, and Oats.
Add melted Margarine gradually while stirring; cover with date mixture.
Then sprinkle with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Pat down in two cookie sheets. Bake at 350 for 10 - 15 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Let ice cream soften slightly.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreo cookies by hand into bite size chunks and add to ice cream mixture.
Place into a Tupperware container and freeze.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble ground beef and sausage into 3-quart casserole.
Stir in onion and garlic.
Cover and cook with glass lid.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cover.
Microwave for 30 to 35 minutes on Medium or simmer or until hot (160°F).
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: pepper steak
directions: Lightly brown steak in butter.
Add vegetables and salt, stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water and soy sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir until sauce is thick and slightly transparent.
Serve over rice.

title: fried catfish
directions: Sprinkle both sides of fish with salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and blend in milk.
Dip fish in the eggs and roll in cornmeal. Place fish in a heavy frypan which contains about 1/8-inch melted fat, hot but not smoking.
Fry at moderate heat.
When fish is brown on one side, turn and brown other side.
Cooking time is about 10 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve immediately.

title: southern buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Add melted butter and buttermilk.
Stir quickly.
Do not knead.
Pat to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Split chilies; rinse out, seed and drain.
Mix cheese; reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Alternate layers of remaining cheese, chilies and egg mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake in oven at 357° for one hour or until cooked through.

title: coconut snow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to the directions on the box. Add coconut pecan icing and mix well. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove cake from pan and allow to cool completely. Ice with whipped cream and top with shredded coconut.

title: pimento-nut dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Stir in olives, nuts, pimento and pepper.
Cover bowl; chill 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve as dip for potato chips, etc.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: kentucky chocolate pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.	Pour into pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring 1 cup water to a boil.
Add margarine. Stir until melted. Remove from burner.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Add eggs and stir until smooth.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, up the sides with dough. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and pat down bubbles (big bubbles!).
Prepare pudding as directed. Add cream cheese.
(I beat cream cheese separately to make it smooth.)
Spread pudding mixture on crust. Set 10 minutes in refrigerator.
Cover with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave fudge
directions: For a Mexican Chili Dog, roll up a hot dog inside a flour tortilla.
Top with chili and cheese.
Heat in microwave.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch square pan.
Combine oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut into butter.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in uncovered, greased casserole dish at 375° for 40 minutes (or 16 minutes in the microwave oven, stirring 3 times during cooking).

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine with cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish, onion powder, salt and liquid smoke; mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
