Shape into ball; roll in mixture of pecans and parsley.
Chill well.

title: emily's easy dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut in desired size (chunks, slices, etc.) Put back in jar and add sugar, vinegar and alum.
Shake until sugar is dissolved.
Store in refrigerator 1 to 2 days before serving. Don't use kosher dills.

title: summer fruit trifle
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions using water and egg whites.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool on wire rack. Cut half the cake into 1-inch cubes (freeze or reserve remaining cake for another use).
Process strawberries in blender or food processor until smooth.
Stir in NutraSweet Spoonful.
Layer 1/3 of the cake cubes in bottom of 2-quart glass serving bowl.
Spoon 1/3 of the milk custard and strawberry puree over cake and top with 1/3 of the raspberries, nectarines, banana and blueberries.
Repeat layers 2 times.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Garnish with whipped topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans and cook until tender.
Mix in catsup and brown sugar.
Put in casserole dish and put slices of bacon on top and bake in oven at 350° for about 35 minutes or until bacon is done. Do not cover.

title: family fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and butter and bring to boil. Boil for six minutes with a rolling boil, stirring constantly.

title: chocolate chip cheese squares
directions: Split chocolate chip roll in half.
Roll out or cut in sections 1/2 of dough; place on bottom of greased square pan. Beat cream cheese, egg, vanilla and sugar together.
Pour into pan on top of dough.
Roll out, or cut in sections second half of chocolate chip roll.
Layer on top of mixture.
Add extra chips. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: holiday sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Beat the eggs, sugar, orange juice and vanilla.
Turn into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Return to oven until marshmallows are golden brown, about 10 minutes more.

title: sausage baked with sweet potatoes 'n' apples
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and cut into thin slices.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and cover bottom with half the sweet potatoes.
Shape sausage into 8 flat cakes and brown lightly.
Drain on paper towels.
Peel apples and cut into thick slices.
Place sausage on sweet potatoes in casserole dish and cover with all of the apples.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and brown sugar.
Place remaining potatoes on apples.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: no bake peach pie
directions: Mix and pour in graham cracker pie shells.
Refrigerate or may be frozen.	Makes 2 pies.

title: pizza snack
directions: Spread pizza sauce on bread, sprinkle Parmesan cheese on sauce and add pepperoni and cheese.
Toast in oven until cheese melts.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Beat all ingredients at one time on medium speed, approximately 25 minutes.
Put in cold ungreased pan.
Turn on oven, 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: tropical stuffed cornish hens
directions: Saute onions, drained pineapple (heat juice with jelly), nuts, rice, ginger, currants and broth.
Spoon 2/3 cup in each fowl. Roast one hour and ten minutes at 350°.
Baste with jelly mixture.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Spread lightly beaten yolk over crust and bake at 375° until brown, about 5 minutes.

title: filet mignon au poivre
directions: Coarsely crush whole peppercorns and roll filet in until all pepper has adhered to steak; you may need to push in some with your hands.
This can be done in advance and kept in refrigerator until ready to prepare.

title: stuffed cherry peppers
directions: Drain peppers; set brine aside.
Cut off tops and scoop seeds out of peppers.
Roll slices of cheese and Prosciutto and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Stuff into peppers spiral side up.
Place in deep sided dish.
Mix olive oil, brine, oregano, salt and pepper and drizzle over peppers.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken. Remove chicken from broth. Break vermicelli into small pieces and add to chicken broth - cook until done - set aside - vermicelli will soak up excess chicken broth. Cook onions and bell peppers in margarine and Worcestershire sauce until done. Debone chicken, taking out all the funky stuff. Pour vermicelli into large baking dish, add Velveeta, chicken, onions and bell peppers and tomatoes. Stir well. Mix in peas. Bake at 375° until cheese is melted completely. Usually 10-15 minutes will work. Makes a huge bowl. MUST BE SERVED WITH CORNBREAD!

title: robert redford's whole wheat quick bread
directions: Combine egg with buttermilk, molasses or honey and melted butter.
Mix together whole wheat flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir into wet mixture.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Spoon into 2 small, greased loaf pans or 1 large one. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chicken durango
directions: Mix all ingredients accept chicken.
Marinate chicken for 3-4 hours if time permitting.
Bake uncovered at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or on top of potatoes.

title: cherry cloud
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper.
Pat into 10-inch pie plate as a crust.
Place frozen potatoes on top.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger with onions.
Add all the ingredients except cheese and mix well.
Put 1/2 mixture in baking dish; add 1 cup cheese and then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Boil until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Mix well, then add 2 quarts fresh peaches.
Divide filling between two pie shells. Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and corn flakes.
Place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed corn flakes and then melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 250° oven for one hour, stirring with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.

title: leek rings
directions: Slice white portion of leeks into 1/4-inch slices.
Separate rings (they'll look like mini-onion rings).
Mix flour, Bisquick, seasoned salt and cayenne pepper together in a bowl.
Pour half of a bottle of beer (or so) into another bowl.
Dip out 10 leek rings at a time into the beer, then into the flour mixture.
Shake off excess flour.
Fry rings in peanut oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot.

title: my favorite dessert
directions: Melt butter, mix in flour and pecans and press in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 5 to 10 minutes (golden brown).
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 to 3/4 of a box of confectioners sugar.
Pour over cooked crust.
I take fresh strawberries and mix with strawberry glaze and pour over Cool Whip mixture and refrigerate before serving.
You can put the following on top of the Cool Whip mixture.

title: lemon delicacy
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, lemon juice, rind and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased casserole and set dish in pan of water.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
May be served warm or cold, with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the water and Miracle Whip in a bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients in order.
Mix after each addition.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until done, in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans.

title: mash potatoes the night before
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add butter, some garlic salt, pepper, cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well and store in refrigerator overnight.
Heat in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: venison with mushrooms
directions: Pound venison with a meat mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour and fry in butter for 8 to 10 minutes, turning a few times.
Remove meat from saucepan and set aside. Add wine, cloves, salt, pepper and sour cream to the drippings. Simmer for 10 minutes and strain.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, drained salsa and sour cream together.
Chill. Serve with corn chips.

title: scratch corn bread
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients, then add oil, eggs and milk. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Cook wheat in water for a few minutes.
Squeeze out excess water.
Mix all ingredients together and serve with lettuce or parboiled cabbage leaves.

title: homemade beefstick
directions: Mix with hands and roll into cracker-size balls.
Wrap in plastic and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake on rack at 300°
for 90 minutes.

title: mexican subs
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low 6 hours or until meat is very tender.
Serve on large sandwich rolls with mayonnaise and Mozzarella cheese. Also good served rolled up in soft tortilla shells.

title: zella's tuna casserole
directions: Mix and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cream of chicken soup can be substituted for mushroom soup.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until ball forms, then add 1/2 stick of butter.
Add pecans, if desired.
Pour onto a buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Mix pineapple and jello in saucepan and heat until jello is dissolved.
(Do not add any water!)
After jello is dissolved, remove from heat and cool.
Add cottage cheese.
Place in refrigerator until jello begins to set.
Add Cool Whip and return to refrigerator until completely set.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix together and drop on a cookie sheet by tablespoons.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef lightly.
Drain off any fat.
Mix together all ingredients.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Put in plastic containers and freeze.

title: morsel-mallow fudge
directions: Place cream cheese in a deep bowl and cream until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend in sugar.
Add salt and melted morsels.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and cream.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in marshmallows.
Press into well greased 8-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator until well chilled and firm.
Cut into squares.

title: quick and easy pepper steak
directions: Pound flour into steak with a hammer or edge of saucer.
Brown steak on both sides in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook over low heat until steak is tender.
Stir often. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bahama mama
directions: Mix together and drink.

title: seafood - fennel chowder
directions: Thaw the salmon, scallops and shrimp, if frozen.
Cut salmon into 1/2-inch pieces, discarding skin and bone; set aside.
Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tail intact, if desired.
Remove green wedges; remove cone and discard.
Chop fennel wedges.

title: salami
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except water.
Shape into rolls 2 1/2-inches in diameter (no larger).
Wrap shiny side up in foil.
Chill 24 hours.
Poke holes in bottom of foil.
Place on broiler rack with water in broiler pan.
Bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Unwrap to cool.
Great for any wild game.

title: anadama bread
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add cornmeal slowly.
Cook water and cornmeal together for just a couple of minutes.
Add molasses, salt and shortening.
Cook together until ingredients are well mixed. Start adding sifted flour.
When mixture makes a stiff dough, turn onto a floured surface.
Start kneading, adding flour as needed, until dough is smooth and glossy.
Place dough in a greased bowl. Cover, place in warm spot to rise until doubled.
Poke down and let rise once more.
Turn onto floured surface; let relax 10 minutes. Make into 2 loaves.
Place in loaf pans, cover and let rise until about doubled.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, reduce heat and bake 20 minutes more at 325°.
Cool on rack.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend for 2 minutes.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Cover 4 to 5 pound pot roast with garlic powder.
Salt and pepper top and bottom.
Place in slow cooker with1/2 cup water. Place 2 medium size onions, sliced, over top.
Let cook all night on medium heat with onions sliced over top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together.
Makes a medium size casserole bowl.

title: shrimp creole-louisiana
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for the cheese.
Put in lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese across the top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
Smear on top when bread is done baking.

title: brunch puff
directions: Cook bacon; crumble.
Cook
onions
in	bacon drippings until soft.
Spread half bread quarters in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with half	of bacon, cheese and onions.
Repeat layers. Combine eggs, milk,
salt
and pepper.
Pour over top bread. Store 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake
at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour; continue beating until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1/2 hour.
Stir down batter and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Let rise until double, about 1/2 hour.
Heat oven to 400°. Bake about 15 minutes.

title: cheese coins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well to form dough. Divide dough in half, and roll each half into a log.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill or freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions; cut out root end in wedge.
Insert beef bouillon cube, salt, pepper and seal top of hole with butter or margarine. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: mr. d.'s easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Add sauce and water; heat in skillet.
Mix the cottage cheese, egg, parsley and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Spread 1/2 cup of sauce and meat on bottom of casserole.
Put a row of noodles on top, then cheese, then sauce, etc.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and add some Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: venna's scalloped potatoes(very good!)
directions: If using fresh potatoes, after boiling, cool and peel, then grate on large grater; set aside.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well in between each egg.
Add sour cream.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients and flavoring.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: apple rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 1-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chef's deluxe cheesecake
directions: Keep ingredients out of refrigerator for one hour before starting to bake.
Heat oven for 10 minutes at 400°.
Butter and flour pan.
Put tin foil around outside bottom and sides of 9-inch or 10-inch spring-from pan before baking.
Mix well with mixer until very smooth.
May take as long as 5 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350°.
Bake cake 1 hour.
Shut off oven and leave cake in oven for 1 more hour with door open.
Leave cake out on rack at least 3 to 4 before refrigerating at least 12 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a full boil.
Boil 1 minute exactly.
Turn off heat and immediately add cocoa, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by spoonful onto waxed paper. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: lemon shrimp scampi
directions: In a small skillet heat olive oil over medium heat.
Stir in garlic.
Add shrimp and cook about 3 minutes until they curl and turn pink.
Stir in parsley and lemon.
Toss a few seconds.
Then season with pepper.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix batter and pour half into tube pan (grease and flour pan). Sprinkle with sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Take spoon and swirl into batter.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before starting next layer.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Rinse several times; add peas to water with onion, garlic, celery and shortening.
Cover and cook for 1 hour on medium heat.
Turn down low; add ham, seasoning and bay leaves.
Cover and cook for 2 hours more or until done.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, dry mustard and pepper until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat to lowest setting and stir in 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese until melted.

title: pecan butter balls (cookies)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt; work in butter and vanilla.
Add 2 cups of nuts; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake cookies in a slow oven, 325°, for about 25 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in fine granulated sugar (I prefer to use powdered sugar).
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut peanut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in butter.
Mix together with next 3 ingredients.
Add chili sauce, salt and pepper to your liking.
Put a little chili sauce on top of loaf and bake.

title: chicken casserole no. 3
directions: Crumble
box crackers in bottom of casserole dish. Pour mixed ingredients on top, crumble other 1/2 crackers over mixture. Chop
stick of oleo on this.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple in bowl, add instant pudding (dry) into pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook until well blended.
Add bay leaf, onions, peppers, garlic, parsley, thyme, green onions, salt, pepper and shrimp; mix well.
Cook for 5 minutes, then add tomatoes and water and cook for 30 minutes, stirring often, or until sauce is thickened.
Discard bay leaf.
Add Tabasco sauce. Serve over hot rice.

title: granita de caffe(frozen coffee and cream)
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil and cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Cool; mix with the coffee.
Pour into refrigerator tray (2 trays may be needed, depending upon size) and freeze without stirring until granular.
Serve in sherbet glasses with whipped cream on top or spoon alternately coffee ice and whipped cream into parfait glass and finish off with whipped cream on top.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening, then add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, salt and milk and mix.
Boil 1/2 cup water and add Hershey's cocoa.
Add to other ingredients and mix.
Pour batter into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Peel and slice enough potatoes to line a 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Spread ground beef over potatoes.
Drain green beans and add a layer of them.
Mix soup with 1 can milk and then pour over casserole evenly.
Season to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle onions on top and return, uncovered, to oven for 5 minutes.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to pkg. directions; drain.
In bowl, beat eggs well; add cooked noodles. In another bowl mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Melt butter; add to noodle mixture; add flour mixture, raisins, pineapple with juice, apples, orange juice and grated skin and almond extract.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Roll biscuits on floured board; press into an ungreased muffin cup, making sure dough goes up to edge of cup. Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Scramble hamburg and drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni and add to hamburg mixture.

title: deneen's fruit dip
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add pineapple juice.
Cook until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs and sugar.
Place on heat until thick.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip. Serve with favorite fresh fruits.

title: original fruit soup
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until tapioca is thick and clear. Cool.
Make thick enough so other juices can be added.
Adjust to your taste.
This makes the "base."
Base keeps 1 week in refrigerator.
When chilled, add fresh or frozen strawberries, peaches, pineapple, fresh pears, melons, etc.
Add bananas near serving time.
Bananas and pears give a mellow flavor.

title: black-eyed pea skillet dinner
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat until beef is browned; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with party pumpernickel bread.

title: chicken 'n beer
directions: Saute chopped garlic in a little oil in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour and sugar until well blended.
Blend in butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for one hour. Serve with vanilla ice cream, Cool Whip or whipped cream.
May be eaten warm or cold.

title: chicken bake
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix both cans of soup with 1 soup can of broth.
Pour on top of chicken.
Mix packets of stuffing mix with 1 cup chicken broth or the remainder of can.
Spoon on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream for 5 minutes.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Combine egg crumb mixture, onion and seasonings.
Add meat and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls (chill meat for easier handling).
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove from skillet and reserve drippings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended (best if mixed by hand in large bowl).
Store in airtight container.
To make an 8-ounce cup, measure one scoop of mix (I use leftover plastic scoops from coffee cans or powdered drink mix) into bottom of 8-ounce cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla; add gelatin and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together; pack 2/3 of mixture on bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.

title: microwavable marshmallow truffles
directions: Arrange marshmallows on a tray; freeze for 15 minutes. Microwave chips in microwavable bowl on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every minute.
Dip marshmallows into chocolate, turning until coated.
Roll in pecans or sprinkles.
Place on wax paper-lined tray.
Refrigerate or keep in a cool place.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to
and butter baking dish.	Chop up artichokes and mix	in Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and dash of Worcestershire sauce,
garlic
salt and Tabasco sauce.
Put in baking dish and bake
for
20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly on top.
Serve with cut-up pita bread or pumpernickel.

title: jelly roll
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan or spray with Baker's Joy.
Beat eggs with rotary beater or mixer until thick.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in water and vanilla all at once.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and beat in all at once.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Bake just until cake tests done. Loosen edges and immediately turn upside-down on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Spread cake at once with soft whipped jelly and roll up, beginning at short end.
Wrap in the towel until cool (1/2 hour).

title: reuben pizza
directions: Place the crust on a 14-inch pizza pan; spread with salad dressing. Layer with corned beef and sauerkraut. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Bring to a rapid boil the cocoa, margarine, Crisco, buttermilk and water.
Gradually beat this hot mixture into the dry ingredients to blend.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat to blend.
Pour into a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove and at once spread the frosting.
Cool.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix; spread on crust.
Top with broccoli, cauliflower and cherry tomatoes (cut in half).
Top with shredded carrots.

title: lemon crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. If desired, top each cookie with a pecan half. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute before removing to cookie rack to finish cooling.

title: ketchup dip
directions: Combine all in blender until thick and refrigerate.
Serve with chips of choice.

title: emily's vegetable soup
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer over low heat for an hour to bring out flavor.
You can add a 1/4 cup of whole, fresh goat's milk, if desired.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, water, peanut butter, oleo or butter and cake mix until smooth (will be really thick).
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown and tests done.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: iced mint drink
directions: Pound mint leaves to a pulp.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and pound again.
Make a syrup by boiling 2 1/2 pints of water with remaining sugar for 5 minutes.
Take pan off heat; allow to cool. Add the lemon juice and mint pulp.
Stir well together.
Chill for several hours.

title: south of the border chicken(serves 2)
directions: Combine cornmeal, pepper and garlic in shallow bowl.
Combine buttermilk and pepper.
Dip chicken breast in milk mixture, then in cornmeal mix.
Place on nonstick baking sheet.
Drizzle teaspoon oil over each breast.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 425° oven until tender.
Each serving has 4 P, 1 B, 1/4 V, 1 F and 10 optional calories.

title: aggie slush punch
directions: Mix juices with sugar and freeze.
Two hours before the punch is to be served, remove from freezer and let thaw.
Right before serving, scoop thawed juice into punch bowl and pour ginger ale into the bowl.
The ginger ale will cause the frozen juice to melt even quicker.
Stir thoroughly and break up large chunks of ice. Punch will be mushy.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour and mix like pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients about 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Can add Italian cheese if desired.
Serves 8.
Is great for lunch, dinner or a party.

title: grandma's chop suey
directions: Brown round steak.
Add celery and onion and juice from canned vegetables.
Add molasses, bouillon, water and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/4 cup water with 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Mix into chop suey and cook until thickened about 2 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in the bottom of a greased dish.
Brown the ground beef.
Drain and spoon into dish of Doritos.
Sprinkle the chopped onion on top of ground beef.
Add 1/2 of the grated cheese. Add the 2 kinds of soups, tomatoes and water.
Take a spatula and run through to mix.
Grate the rest of the cheese on top and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine lemon or lime juice and condensed milk.
Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crumb crust or cooled pastry shell.
Add whipped cream for topping, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: crystal pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar; continue creaming.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk.
Begin and end with flour.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon filling for layer cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add grated rind, lemon juice and egg, slightly beaten. Put butter in saucepan.
When melted, add mixture and stir constantly until boiling point is reached. Care must be taken that mixture does not adhere to bottom of saucepan. Cool before spreading.
(A little cream may be added.)

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, green beans, cream of mushroom soup and chopped onion together.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dice hot dogs into small quarters and lay over mixture.
Lightly sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana-strawberry popsicles
directions: Combine banana and strawberry yogurt together in blender. Whirl until smooth.
Pour into popsicle molds; freeze until firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to softball stage. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens.
Pour in pan; refrigerate.

title: boss hog stew
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers.
Add smoked sausage, zucchini and corn.
Cook on medium heat for about 30 minutes in covered dish, stirring occasionally.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Set aside.
Brown meat with green peppers and onion.
Add noodles, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Mix together.
Put in 13 x 9 pan.
Top with the three cheeses and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple macaroon
directions: Put apples in buttered casserole.
Add sugar and cinnamon and dot with oleo.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Cream together oleo, egg and Sweet 'N Low.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate, stirring in each.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix sugar with flour.
Make well in center and add Crisco and yeast.
Make up with buttermilk and yeast mixture; knead well. Oil ball of dough and put in oiled, tightly covered bowl. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all together in casserole dish.
Flake margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir once or twice as it cooks.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Puree strawberries in blender.
Combine eggs and oil in small bowl and whisk thoroughly.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar (6 to 8 minutes) to soft ball stage.
Pour over butter and chocolate chips.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Pour in greased pan.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: ground meat soup
directions: Combine meat, covered with water, onion and green pepper; boil.
Cut carrots and potatoes; cook 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Add paprika and salt.
Can add split peas now.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries in a cooked pie shell.
Refrigerate until congealed. Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Roll into a ball, then roll ball into pecans and parsley flakes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, pudding, sugar, water, oil and eggs well.
Add chocolate chips and sour cream.
Mix.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour.

title: edna's cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple (or any fruit) well.
Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip, drained fruit and jello (dry from the package).
Mix gently.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until it sets.

title: summer fruit cake
directions: Day before serving:
In blender at low speed, finely grind almonds; set aside.
In small bowl with beater at high speed, blend cream cheese and 5 tablespoons milk until smooth and fluffy. Beat in 1/2 cup ground almonds and sugar.
With wooden spoon, stir in grapes, pecans and almonds.
In small bowl with fork, mix together bread crumbs, remaining ground almonds and lemon peel. Add 1 tablespoon milk and toss with two forks until mixture begins to stick together.
Line bottom and sides of 8 x 5-inch pan with waxed paper.
Press 1/2 crumb mixture into bottom.
Spread 1/3 cheese mixture over crumbs and arrange 3/4 of fruit on top. Gently press fruit halfway into mixture.
Add about 1 1/3 cups of cheese and press remaining fruit into it.
Smooth rest of cheese over fruit and sprinkle remaining crumbs evenly over top.
Fold waxed paper extensions over cake; press down firmly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spiced orange tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea, cloves, orange peel and cinnamon in heatproof container.
Cover and let stand until desired strength, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir and strain.
Makes 6 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook together beef, pork and onion in 1 cup chicken stock and just enough water to cover meat.
Cook in a heavy cooker for 1 hour or in a slow cooker for longer time.
Salt to taste.
Add catsup and tomatoes; cook another hour.
Add corn, chicken and red pepper.
Cook slowly another hour and stir often.
Complete cooking time is three hours.
Cook, uncovered, after corn is added to allow to thicken.
One teaspoon of liquid smoke gives a barbecued flavor.
Yields 15 servings.

title: plain pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, flavoring, egg and margarine.
Mix until slightly lumpy.
Fry in moderately hot skillet until golden brown, using oil in skillet.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape in patties.
In large skillet, melt butter and add cakes.
Brown on both sides.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake in a greased tube pan at 370° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: You also need 1 new 8-inch flowerpot, cleaned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in oil, pumpkin, eggs, nuts and raisins. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (makes 2 loaves). Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cajun pork chops
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan with foil or a baking bag.
Trim pork chops and place in bottom of dish.
(Place water in bottom of dish to prevent drying of pork chops.)
Cover each pork chop with mustard.
Pour gumbo over entire dish.
Cover with foil or baking bag.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frank's mohawk valley chili
directions: Saute meat in big frying pan; drain fat.
Do not overcook the meat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice; saute meat until brown with 1 teaspoon oil, then add onion, salt, pepper and parsley.
Scramble egg and add to mixture.
Cook garlic with onion.
Take off heat and add soy sauce.
Serve with pepper steak or use as any side dish.
Serves 4.

title: nacho cheeseburgers
directions: Make hamburger patties.
Grill.
During last minute, spoon 1 tablespoon of mild or spicy cheese sauce onto each patty.
Cover; grill until cheese starts to melt.

title: celestial chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around the chicken.
Place chicken in greased, shallow casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour soup mixture over it.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash fritters
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Mash.
Mix all ingredients together and fry in deep oil like frying hush puppies.

title: butter coffeecake
directions: Mix all together in the order given, then beat for 8 minutes. Mix filling of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put 1/2 of the batter in a prepared Bundt pan.
Pour the cinnamon filling over the batter, then pour the rest of the cake batter on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly and then turn out on a cake plate.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water and ice cubes and set aside until you grind the following ingredients:
cranberries, oranges, celery and apples.
Add sugar and mix together with jello.
Let set.
(Can be frozen.)

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased corn-size cans, 8 ounce size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: campers chili
directions: In a large pot, add tomatoes, juice, onion, pepper and ground beef (do not brown ground beef). Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add water, if needed.
Stir often. Add chili beans and kidney beans with salt, garlic, chili powder, cumin and smart season. Add more chili powder or cayenne for hotter chili.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Thaw spinach souffl mix with eggs. Mix in grated cheese, sausage, mushrooms, etc. Mix well and pour into frozen pie crust. Bake at 350° to 375° (depending on your oven) for 35 to 45 minutes or longer. Bake until top is browned.

title: cheesy egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat together the ingredients.
Put in baking dish (sprayed with Pam, 9 x 13-inch dish).
Refrigerate overnight.
Do not cover in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. They'll love it.

title: chocolate covered candy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and paraffin.
Roll this mixture into marble size balls.
Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
As you slowly simmer, dip the candy balls in and coat with chocolate.
Let them cool on a sheet of waxed paper.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, stock, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, then simmer until the broccoli is cooked.
(Mash with potato masher if desired.)

title: cream cheese treats
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter together until well blended.
Add flour and lemon; mix well.
Form into four balls of equal size; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.
Roll out one ball at a time between two sheets of waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out with 2 1/2-inch round scalloped-edge cookie cutter (or plain cutter).
Place cookies on ungreased baking sheets.
On one side of cookie, cut out 1-inch wide heart with cookie cutter 1/4-inch from the edge (may be omitted).
Place a small amount of preserves on the other side of cookie.
Fold cookie in half and press edges together.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly puffed and just beginning to brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheets.
Yields approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: microwave chicken and gravy
directions: Place chicken in microwave dish and cover with soup.
Place plastic wrap over dish and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over and cook for another 10 minutes.
Great served with rice or potatoes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Add half the flour, beat well. Add sour cream; beat well. Add remaining flour and flavorings; beat well. Take butter and grease a tube pan. Sprinkle pan with sugar; pour off excess. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and ten minutes or longer. Use a cake tester.

title: portuguese red bean soup
directions: Soak dried red beans overnight.
Drain beans and cover them with fresh water in a saucepan.
Simmer beans until tender, about 2 hours.
Peel and dice potatoes, put them in a soup kettle.
Add fourth teaspoon salt and cook 15 minutes.
Saute onions and garlic in bacon fat until golden.
Add onions and garlic to soup kettle. Add kidney beans and liquid, bay leaves, smoked salt, pepper, allspice and tomato paste.
Let soup simmer 3 hours, adding more water as necessary.
Adjust seasonings and serve soup hot.
I use Spice Island hickory smoke salt for seasoning.
Be careful you don't get too much in it.

title: arjer's scotch shortbread
directions: Grease two 8-inch pie pans and set aside.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Set bacon aside.
Add chopped potatoes, onion, carrot and celery to bacon drippings. Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the milk, salt and pepper; bring mixture to boiling.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: In saucepan, combine seasoning, salt, water and vinegar. Bring to
a boil.
Add shrimp, stir gently.
Cover; steam until tender. Drain, remove shell and vein on back.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Beat eggs; add salt, mustard, milk and onion.
Break bread into chunks and add to mixture with cheese. Add meat.
Place in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, take out and let stand until room temperature.
Add topping, if desired.
Bake casserole in a pan of water at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add lemon juice and rind.
Beat in egg yolks and flour; mix well.
Add milk gradually; beat until well blended.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until center of pie is firm, about 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate rolls and press into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Spoon the sausage over dough; sprinkle with hash browns and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper over the sausage.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake 5 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Slice potatoes and place in bottom of greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Brown pork chops and layer over potatoes.
Slice onion and cover pork chops.
Mix 3 cups water with dry onion soup mix. Pour over everything.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama rains' tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet quick (400° to 450°) about 15 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Prebake piecrust at 400° for 7 minutes.
Drain and set aside until ready to use.
In medium size bowl, blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onions and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight if desired.
Spoon into prebaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes, until inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve hot.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Shake nuts in egg white mixture.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, brown sugar and white sugar and pour on wet nuts and shake.
Pour nuts onto greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir 2 or 3 times, then cool and store in airtight jar.

title: french strawberry glace pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull 1 quart strawberries.
Simmer together about 3 minutes 1 cup strawberries and 2/3 cup water.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water; add to boiling mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
If desired, spread cream cheese on bottom of cooled baked pie shell.
Save out 1/2 cup choice berries for garnish.
Put remaining 2 1/2 cups berries in baked pie shell.
Cover with cooked mixture and garnish with the 1/2 cup berries.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add 7-Up and beat well.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage and ground beef casserole
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in a baking dish. Pour tomato juice over and cover. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in foil lined iron skillet.
Pour in batter. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 425° oven.
(Depending on oven, it may require additional time.)

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and tomato juice.
Stir in bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef; mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat to a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Reserve 1 slice cheese for top.
Tear up or lay slices of cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam-side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done (about 1 1/4 hours).
Center of roll will be pink due to meat.
Cut slice of cheese into 4 triangles; place on top of loaf.
Serves 8.

title: "all you need" breakfast drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until all ingredients are pureed.
Voila!

title: bread pudding
directions: *May also use leftover biscuits.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into pieces.
In a bowl mix 1 cup mayonnaise, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 can cream of chicken soup and 8 ounces of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Add water until mixture is of a medium texture.
Line chicken in bottom of a deep dish casserole.
Put broccoli on top.
Pour liquid mixture over the top.
Fry croutons in butter until brown.
Put on top of liquid mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour out on wire rack to cool.

title: doodle cake
directions: Beat with mixer until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare the following icing.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Melt butter.
Stir with macaroni in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered at 225° for 3 hours.

title: apricot deluxe
directions: Drain apricots and arrange in the bottom of a baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon peel, orange peel and sugar.
Pour whipping cream on top and add almonds.
Bake at 200° for 10 to 20 minutes until warm. Serve immediately.

title: mrs. eleanor graves' fruit racks
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened. Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides of loaf to loosen.
Remove from pan.

title: sherried sweet potatoes
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat sweet potatoes, salt and water (enough to cover the potatoes).
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, until tender.
Drain and peel potatoes.
Mix the sweet potatoes and butter on low speed.
Add remaining ingredients and mix on medium speed until light and fluffy.

title: two step potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until almost tender; cool.
Peel and grate.
In 9 x 12-inch baking dish put grated potatoes; sprinkle dry ingredients over potatoes.
Also sprinkle cheese over the top. Pour over top the heavy cream.
Bake at 350° until browned and tender (30 to 45 minutes).

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello, tapioca pudding and water in saucepan. Boil until jello is dissolved and tapioca is tender. Cool. Add mandarin oranges. Put in a bowl and chill until set. When ready to serve, blend in whipped cream. Serves 8.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine and blend well.
Store in jar.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.
Add boiling water.

title: mint ice
directions: Add 1 cup of sugar to the water.
Boil for 5 minutes; cool. Add the lemon juice and mint syrup.
Freeze.
When frozen, take out, put in bowl and beat, then add 2 egg whites, beaten stiff. Freeze again and serve.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese. Stir until completely blended. Add fruit, nuts and Cool Whip. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Put into pot and add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in beef, garlic, salt, flour, pepper and paprika. Saute additional 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Add sour cream. Heat through.
Serve over noodles, mashed potatoes, rice or toast.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef with first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Mix tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard together.
Put 1/2 in hamburger mixture and save remaining 1/2 for top of meat loaf after you put it in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Bake on 2nd rack level above burner so it won't burn.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and remove bones.
Separate eggs; beat whites and yolks, then fold whites into yolks.
Add crackers, onions, then egg mixture and milk to salmon.
Stir.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes until surface doesn't dent.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine cocoa, sugar and milk.
Add 2 sticks of margarine and bring to a boil.
Boil hard for two minutes.
Pour over the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and drop with a spoon.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, and set aside.
Mix next 2 ingredients together; set aside.

title: pesto
directions: Place basil, oil, garlic and 1/4 cup of pine nuts in a food processor; process for about 15 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve over warm pasta.

title: chicken creole
directions: Place shortening, flour, onions, green pepper and parsley in large skillet.
Cook until onions are brown; add tomatoes, chopped celery, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Add cooked chicken and cover; cook slowly for 1 hour.
One half hour before done, add Worcestershire sauce.
Serve over cooked rice and sprinkle with chow mein noodles or serve separately.
Serves 6.

title: chow mein (hamburger)
directions: (Optional: Can also add 1 (14 ounce) can La Choy meatless chow mein.)

title: paralee sargent's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually.
Beat mixture until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour with mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Start in a cool oven and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on a rack.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Place
pork
chops
in
baking
dish, season with salt, pepper and
garlic salt.
Sprinkle rice over pork chops along with onions,
tomatoes and tomato soup.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Boil 2 1/2 pounds pork roast with salt, pepper and onion for 1 hour.
Add tomato soup and boil one more hour.
Add one small head of shredded cabbage and sauerkraut; simmer on low heat for another couple of hours.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain well. Put vegetables in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over top.
Cut cheese in small pieces.
Stir with fork.
Cover with stuffing.
Dribble margarine over all of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit glazed cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until just set; cool.
Drain fruits thoroughly; arrange in circle on chilled pie.
Stir marmalade; spoon over fruits to glaze.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into lengthwise pieces.
Dissolve salt in 1 gallon of boiling water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand one week.
During that time, stir once every day.
At the end of a week, drain off salt water and cover with clear boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain off water.
Dissolve alum in 1 gallon boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours, then drain off.	Heat vinegar and sugar very hot.
Pour over cucumbers. Let stand 24 hours.
Pour liquid off into pan.
Reheat to boiling and pour back over cucumbers 4 times, waiting 24 hours between each time.
On the fifth day, can pickles.
Add pickling spices when vinegar is heated.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Pour lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk in bowl.
Mix and let thicken.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip and pour into crusts. Chill overnight.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Spread with marshmallow cream on top while hot.
Spread with chocolate icing when cool.

title: crawfish stew
directions: Melt oleo in iron skillet.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic, parsley and green onions.
Saute well for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour and paprika.
Add crawfish.
Add water.
Stir and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: lil' pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flatten biscuits.

Spread pizza sauce on biscuits. Cut pepperoni into small pieces and place over pizza sauce. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until biscuits are browned and cheese melts. Watch closely. (I put the pepperoni in the microwave for a few seconds and blot with paper towels to remove excess grease.)

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese with sugar until smooth and light. Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch
only until thoroughly mixed. Stir in sour cream until well blended.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is dry.

title: jello cakes
directions: Heat 1 cup of water to boiling.
Stir in the jello until it dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Add second cup of water.
When cool, add the fruit, if desired.
Pour into cupcake pans and cool in the refrigerator until set.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Cook leeks and peeled sliced potatoes in chicken broth, covered, until tender.
Run through food mill or sieve or blender. Return to pot and add other ingredients (except chives and paprika).
Do not boil after you add the milk and cream.
Serve either hot or cold and garnish with the chives and paprika. Serves 4.

title: campbell's 15 minute chicken & rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until brown. Remove chicken.
Add to skillet soup, water, paprika and pepper. Heat to boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Top with chicken. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shearing cake(actually a wonderfully flavored, easy to make quick bread.)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg in large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in sugars and lemon peel.
In small bowl beat eggs and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix with wooden spoon just until flour mixture is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve slightly warm and thinly sliced.

title: model t three pedal fish soup
directions: Wash shrimp; add boiling water and the seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Shell shrimp and remove black vein.
Cook onion in butter for 3 or 4 minutes; add tomatoes and shrimp liquid.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add flour mixed to a paste with a little cold water.
Cook until thickened.
Add fish fillets, cut in small pieces; simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and lobster; heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Good with crisp stalks of celery.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: baked frozen peas
directions: Butter a quart casserole; break up frozen peas and mix in soup.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown
onion,
bacon and celery.
Add flour and pint of water to	form
a
roux.	(Calorie counters may eliminate the roux.) The
roux may be frozen for later use.
Cook the potatoes
in about
a
pint
of	water; add roux, milk and garlic powder. Pepper and salt to taste.
Heat and serve.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Rub the chicken with some of the garlic, salt and pepper and refrigerate about 2 hours.
In a Dutch pot, heat oil, saute the chicken, lightly brown.
Remove the chicken, add the potatoes, lightly brown and remove and set aside.
Add the vinegar to the pot and bring to a boil, scraping up browned bits from the bottom of the pot.
Add the chicken, the potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Add the rest of the garlic, jalapeno peppers, cilantro and parsley.
Cover and lower the heat until chicken is very tender.

title: trifle
directions: Cut pieces of cake and place in bottom of large serving bowl (optional:
sprinkle with rum or brandy).
Melt jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Pour over cake.
Cool in fridge.
Make vanilla pudding and pour over jello.
Spoon fruit over pudding.
When ready to serve, cover with whipped cream and garnish with fresh fruit and slivered almonds.
Serve with warm Bird's Eye custard and/or ice cream.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 2-quart covered casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: everything and more(meat; vegetable)
directions: Fry hamburger.
Put in baking dish.
Add 1 can of tomato sauce. Put green beans and corn on top of hamburger.
Put mashed potatoes on top.
Add cheese over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Break up sausage meat into small pieces. Brown in skillet.
Remove and drain.
Saute onion in fat until transparent. Drain.
Combine both into uncooked pastry shell. Sprinkle cheese over all.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook seashells until tender, but firm.
Drain.
Heat sauce, mix with shells.
Add mushrooms and half of pepperoni.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and half of mozzarella cheese. Mix together. Place in buttered casserole dish and top with remaining mozzarella.
Place remaining sliced pepperoni on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diane's potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil in salted water until done (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain and cool.
Boil eggs.
Drain, cool, peel and dice.
Mix potatoes, eggs and onions together in a large bowl. Mix Miracle Whip, mustard and ketchup in a separate bowl.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: sausage and mushroom stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven or casserole, combine all ingredients except cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and stir; add the cabbage, cover again and return to oven for 30 more minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: popover chicken pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and paprika; mix well.
Roll chicken in flour mixture and brown on all sides in shortening or vegetable oil.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towel.

title: texas rice
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onion, and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until soft.
Stir in the rice, green pepper, chili powder, oregano, tomato juice and tomato sauce; then add the water and salt.
Stir once; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed using the milk. Sprinkle half the graham crackers on bottom of pie dish. Top with pudding and half the bananas. Sprinkle half the remaining crumbs and bananas and refrigerate.

title: chiffon cake
directions: In first bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Form a well and add Wesson oil, egg yolks, cold water, vanilla and lemon flavoring. Beat with spoon until smooth.

title: cheesecake archway cookies
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar well. Spread mixture on top of each cookie.
Then add a spoonful of strawberry pie filling to each.

title: sausage cantonese
directions: Cut water chestnuts in quarters.
Cover with sausage.
Make into balls.
Put sausage balls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Serve on toothpicks with sweet hot mustard.

title: favorite layered green salad
directions: In long dish, layer lettuce, onion, celery, water chestnuts and frozen green peas, in this order.
Spread mayonnaise on top. Mix together sugar, salt and pepper and sprinkle over mayonnaise. Last, sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese over mayonnaise and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and sugar; let work.
Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Mix the flour mixture with the yeast mixture.
Let rise once.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet pan.
Spread dough in pan.
Top with sauce and spaghetti cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with favorite toppings.
Bake for 25 more minutes. Let cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Dump first 7 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Stir well with spoon.
Pour into 4 pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 pies or serves 24 people.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook, cool and cut up prunes.
Line angel food cake pan with waxed paper.

title: fullabull's chinese pie
directions: Mix well and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together, then add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls onto 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oats; mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Store in a cool place.

title: mrs. glen's sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch angel cake tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat butter and 2 1/2 cups of the sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and continue beating until mixture is creamy-light; add lemon extract and vanilla.
Beat egg whites in a medium-size bowl until foamy white.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until mixture forms soft glossy peaks.
Stir baking soda into sour cream.
Add flour alternately with sour cream mixture to butter mixture, blending well after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg white mixture until no streaks of white remain.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a slow oven (350°) for 1 hour and 30 minutes until cake tester or wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Loosen around edge and tube; remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: zucchini pie(better than egg custard)
directions: Peel and cook zucchini (6 minutes in microwave).
Blend all ingredients in blender (will be creamy).
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until set.

title: frazalini
directions: In a large skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic with meat; drain.
Add corn, tomato soup and noodles.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add cream cheese.
Pour into a large baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: helen's surprise salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar.
Add this, while hot, to jello which has been dissolved in hot water.
Let cool.
Add cheese and pecans.
Place in refrigerator.
When almost congealed, fold in whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: In medium bowl combine caramel pieces and flour.
Add apples, caramel topping and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked crust.
Top with pecan pieces.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until crust is brown.
Cool.

title: lemon herb chicken
directions: In a large, shallow baking dish, mix lemon juice, oil, herbs and spices.
Add chicken; turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate, turning occasionally, for several hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Grill or broil 6 inches from heat, turning and brushing frequently with marinade, for 35 to 45 minutes, or until tender.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Set it in freezer for 1 hour.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: apple cheddar scones
directions: Grease 8 in. round cake pan.
In medium bowl mix flour, wheat germ, baking powder, salt and sugar.
With two knives or pastry blender cut butter into flour mixture until it is the consistency of crumbs.
Add cheese and apples.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted oleo.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat powdered sugar, 2 sticks oleo and eggs until fluffy.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice bananas on fluffy mixture. Spread desired amount of crushed pineapple over the bananas and top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans and maraschino cherries. Chill and serve.

title: yellow cucumber pickles(canning)
directions: Mix lime in water and stir well.
Soak cucumbers 24 hours. Then wash 6 times in clean water.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add whipping cream from carton; do not whip.
Add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: martha washington
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and Eagle Brand milk.
Work in nuts and coconut.
Chill.
Form balls and chill.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler; stir until smooth.
Dip balls in chocolate coating.

title: christmas eve crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Empty both mix pouches into bowl.
Add egg and maple flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls. Roll into 2-inch cylinders in "crescent" shape, tapering ends slightly.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar immediately. Cool slightly. Roll completely in confectioners sugar while still warm. Makes 36 cookies.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter, soda and oats.
When well blended, add chocolate chips, nuts and M&M's.

title: rainbow ice cream dessert
directions: Cut or tear cake into small pieces.
Divide into thirds and place in medium-size bowls.
Sprinkle strawberry gelatin over one third, lime gelatin over another and orange gelatin over one third.
Toss each lightly with a fork until cake is well coated with gelatin.
In a 10-inch tube pan or angel food pan, put strawberry cake pieces in bottom.
Spoon strawberries over cake. Spread one third ice cream over strawberries.
Repeat layers with lime cake pieces, blueberries, ice cream, orange pieces, mandarin oranges and ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold on a chilled dessert plate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into rings.
Saute in margarine until limp.
Pour half of onions into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with Parmesan cheese, then crushed crackers.
Repeat layer and bake, uncovered, in 325° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp reserving some of the liquid.
Using fork, blend the shrimp into the cream cheese until there are no large chunks of shrimp.
Shape into mound and cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve on crackers.

title: custard pumpkin cake
directions: Combine flour with baking powder, salt and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk and mix.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer.
Add remaining 1/4 cup milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Use rubber spatula.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: golden mushroom sirloin beef tips
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 2 hours or until tender.
Stir now and then. Serve over noodles.

title: aunt phyllis' cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Gradually beat in milk.
Stir in vanilla and juice.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling, if desired.

title: super easy chicken
directions: Rinse chicken under cold water.
Put soup and milk in crock-pot, stirring well.
Add chicken; stir until coated with soup mixture.
Cook on low for approximately 6 hours, or until done.
Serve over your favorite noodles.
Serves 4.

title: ruth's blond-nut brownies
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Stir in well. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.
Very good.

title: mother's yam casserole
directions: In large baking dish layer apple pie filling, yams (amount depends on how many you are feeding).
Mix and pour over vegetables the orange marmalade, apricot preserves and cranberry sauce. Sprinkle with a few nuts.
Pineapple or dates may be added or substituted here.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Brush salmon with oil; sprinkle with pepper.
Place on oiled grill, meat side down.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on meat side.
Turn and cook the rest of the time on the skin side.
Brush meat side with more oil and squeeze lemon or lime juice over the top while the fish continues to cook.

title: creamsicle pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, cream cheese and Tang together until smooth. Put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salt and carrots.
Simmer until the barley is cooked, about 45 minutes.
Season to taste with salt, if needed, and garnish with shredded carrots, if desired.

title: s'mores
directions: Place graham crackers down on baking pan.
Top with chocolate. Top with marshmallow, then graham cracker.
Cook at 350° until slightly melted.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: In a skillet, cook the sausage, mushrooms and onion until done.
Drain and set aside.
In a blender, combine 6 eggs and 3 Tbsp. sour cream for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread 1 c. salsa over the egg mixture. Add the meat mixture.
Top meat mixture with Velveeta, cheddar, and mozzarella cheeses.
Either refrigerate, freeze, or bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: oreo cake
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and spread over Oreo crust.
Mix milk with puddings and spread over cheese layer. Cover with Cool Whip and remaining cookies.
Chill overnight.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Whisk in jello and pudding mixes.
Return to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Fold in oranges, pineapple and cool whip.
Spoon in serving bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: no cook lemon freeze
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter together and place in pie pan. Remove 2 to 4 tablespoons and reserve for topping.
Press until firm on bottom and sides of pan. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Combine with sweetened condensed milk. Add lemon juice and lemon peel. Stir until thickened.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Gradually beat in 3 tablespoons sugar.
Fold gently into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Freeze until firm.

title: world's best catfish stew
directions: Cook bacon until it is tearable and hard, but not too crisp. Saute bell pepper and onion in bacon grease.
Cook potatoes until firm with some Italian seasoning added to water.

Drain water; add chopped stewed tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, mostly drained canned corn, 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning, a tablespoon seasoning salt, minced celery, 1 can tomato puree and heat until it boils.
Cover catfish fillets with water in glass bowl; add teaspoon or more of Italian seasoning and microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain water and chunk up catfish; add to hot stew.
Thicken mixture with tomato paste or an extra can of tomato puree.
Simmer awhile and serve in bowl; pass Tabasco.
Serve with cornbread and rice.

title: sweet sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Let set on counter until mixture is consistency of jelly. Add strawberries, pineapple, and bananas. Mix thoroughly. Stir in pecans. Pour half of gelatin mixture in bowl. Let stand in refrigerator until firm. Spread sour cream on gelatin and then remainder of gelatin. Let congeal.

title: deep south sausage and pinto beans
directions: Fry sausage until brown on all sides.
Drain off all but 3 tablespoons of the fat.
Add onions and green peppers; saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend; simmer 10 minutes and serve hot with cornbread.
Serves 10.

title: microwave pink popcorn balls
directions: In microwave, melt last three ingredients.
Tint pink with a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour melted marshmallow mixture over popcorn and stir gently to coat.
Grease hands well with butter and shape into 10 medium sized balls.
Great for girl's birthday party activity!

title: tex mex dip
directions: *Mixture of 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

title: new orleans jezebel sauce
directions: Mix together; heat on low until blended.
Cool and serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Heat the buttermilk with the chilies, garlic and onions just until small bubbles form around the edges.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Combine egg whites, fat-free cheese, buttermilk and canola oil and blend well.
Add liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan sprayed with nonstick spray and bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In another bowl, beat sugar and oil.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin and mix. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Serve with cream cheese or butter.

title: pecan pies
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour filling into pie shells.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Pies can be frozen for future use.

title: pig eatin' cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until blended.
Bake until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Make icing with crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put icing on cake and serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown the rice in bacon grease.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer until rice is fully cooked.
You may have to add more liquid.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Blend in mayonnaise, garlic and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Marinate above in an airtight foil pouch for 8 to 12 hours or overnight. Cook in 275° oven for 8-12 hours.

title: party pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice with marshmallows until they melt.
Dissolve Jell-O into this.
Let cool until it starts to thicken.
Add pineapple, cheese, nuts and whipping cream.
Fold together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cranberry wreath salad
directions: Mold strawberry jello and relish.
Chill until firm.
Second mold:
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add pineapple syrup.
Chill until syrupy. Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salt.
Add to marshmallow mixture.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Chill until almost soft set. Fold in cream; pour over first layer.
Chill until firm.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the yogurt, mayonnaise, pineapple, poultry seasoning and salt.
Stir in the chicken, grapes, celery, apple, almonds and chives.
Roll up in lettuce leaves or serve with crackers.

title: chew bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until firm to touch and golden brown (about 25 minutes).
Cut into squares.
Makes about 5 dozen squares.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Bake and cool the pie shells.
Cover the bottom of the shells with the sliced bananas.
Beat together the softened cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over the bananas.
Top with the blueberry pie filling.
Chill.

title: butterscotch drops
directions: Melt butterscotch in microwave.
Mix in noodles and peanuts. Drop on plate by the spoonful.
Let cool.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: In skillet saute, onion and garlic in oil.
Add zucchini squash, tomatoes, green pepper and salt and pepper to taste. Cook until tender.
Sprinkle with minced parsley and Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick butterscotch rolls
directions: Put frozen bread into the refrigerator overnight. The next morning, cut bread into cubes and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cubes. Let rise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry hamburger and sausage together.
Add seasoning.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Insert cheese into noodles, then meat, then more cheese.
Put in a greased pan.
Pour remaining sauce over noodles.
Add one can of water.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute margarine, pepper, onion and mushrooms (chopped) in skillet or in baking dish in microwave oven. Add rice and mix. Add the cans of beef consomme.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mint candies
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with flavoring, powdered sugar and food coloring desired.
Press into rubber molds.
Keep refrigerated or frozen.
Makes 25.

title: hello dolly cake
