directions: Melt the butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Over this, spread the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chips and chopped nuts.
Over this, pour the Eagle Brand milk.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal scotties
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In separate bowl, mix oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch bits.
Drop by tablespoon, size of walnut, on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Mix together milk, sugar, eggs and butter. Boil 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients. Grease 9 x 13 pan with butter. Line pan with graham crackers (whole). Pour mixture over crackers and spread evenly. Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Place in baking dish and add soup and milk.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 300° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve over baked rice.

title: rice torta
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute onion, zucchini and parsley in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan with olive oil.
Pour rice mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until top is golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
(Will firm up as it cools.)
Serve as appetizers or side dish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl sugar and flour.
Mix and boil rapidly for 2 to 3 minutes the 1 stick oleo, oil or shortening, 4 tablespoons cocoa and water.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Five minutes before cake is done, mix 1 stick oleo, 4 tablespoons cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: tom's pate
directions: Boil livers with thyme and bay leaves for 20 minutes.
Put in blender with brandy, cloves, nutmeg, salt and mustard.
Pour in melted butter.
Scoop out and mix in a bowl with cream cheese. Add egg whites.
Chill one hour.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Mix well and pat onto bottom of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese, rest of sugar and flour until light and fluffy.
Gradually add lemon juice and egg substitute; beat well.
Add lemon yogurt and mix thoroughly.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until center of cake is set.
Gently run tip of knife between cake and edge of pan.
Cool to room temperature before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: mexican beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Blend in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt. Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Layer rice, beans and meat sauce, beginning and ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with corn chips and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with corn tortillas.

title: crystalled peanuts
directions: Boil nuts, sugar, water and vanilla about 20 minutes (until sugar crystallizes on nuts).
Stir constantly.
Place on large cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: king crab frittata
directions: Thaw, drain and
slice	crab.
Slice
zucchini	and cut slices in half.
Saute zucchini, mushrooms and onion in oil in 9-inch skillet.
Add crab	and
heat
through.
Beat
eggs and blend in seasonings.
Pour
eggs
over crab mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cook over
low heat, lifting the edges to allow the uncooked portion
to
run
underneath.
When set, sprinkle with cheese and place under hot broiler until top is delicately browned.
Cut into wedges
and serve at once.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning packets; refrigerate. Crush noodles from soup mix.
Toss cabbage, sliced onions, noodles and almonds; dress with oil mixture.

title: hurry curry
directions: Cook rice, simmer curry and onions in butter.
Add soup and mix until smooth.
Add sour cream and chicken or shrimp.
Serves 4.

title: chef's fruit salad
directions: Remove seeds and rind from melon.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch chunks. Cut meat and cheese into pieces about 2-inches long and 1/4-inch wide.
Thinly slice scallions, including most of green tops.
Chop mint.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onions and hamburger together.
Add garlic powder and beef soup.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Drain and add tomatoes over top of hamburger mixture.
Put potatoes over top and brush raw egg on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork steaks with apple stuffing
directions: Slowly brown pork steaks on both sides in hot fat.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Cover each steak with a layer of the apple stuffing.
Top with apple half.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork is well done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugars, shortening and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add flour (sifted), soda, vanilla and salt.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour (crisscross).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown lean ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add green beans and can of tomato soup.
Put in greased casserole pan.
Mash potatoes and add cheese. Spoon over meat and bean mixture.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter and add garlic, onions, celery and bell pepper. Saute until onions turn yellow.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add green onions, basil, thyme and shrimp. Cook 15 minutes.

title: cucumbers in cream dressing
directions: Slice cucumber very thin.
Put in bowl and sprinkle with salt. Set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Rinse two or three times in cold water and drain.
Toss with dressing, blending the sour cream, vinegar and paprika.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine granulated sugar and Jif until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of the crumb mixture.
Sprinkle the remaining mixture over the bottom of baked shell.
In medium saucepan, combine the 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Combine egg yolks and milk, stir into granulated sugar mixture until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into the shell. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots; while hot, add mayonnaise, horseradish and onions.
Mix well and serve hot.

title: uncle charlie's slaw
directions: Chop or shred cabbage
and onion.
Mix sugar, vinegar and turmeric. Heat mixture until ready to boil.
Pour over vegetables. Mix thoroughly. This will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.
Cut into thirds.
Crumble up 1/3 in bottom of punch bowl.
Put layer of pudding, pineapple, cherries, nuts and Cool Whip in that order; repeat layers, starting with cake.
On last layer, put nuts on top of Cool Whip.
Cut cherries in small pieces and drain.
Put on top of nuts.
Better if made a few days ahead.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Parboil cubed potatoes. Mix sour cream, celery soup and cut up Velveeta cheese. Layer in crock-pot with potatoes. Cook on high until melted.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Fix jello with hot water.
Then add pineapple and pie filling. Let jell.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Note:
Can use any vegetable you like.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add hot water.
Add rest of ingredients (except angel food cake and Dream Whip).
Refrigerate until firm.
Rub brown off of angel food cake and break into pieces.
Make Dream Whip as directed on package.
Take out 1 cup to use as icing.
Line a colander with clear plastic wrap such as Saran Wrap.
Mix Dream Whip with chilled mixture.
Alternate layers of cake pieces and Dream Whip mixture until all used.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Turn upside down on plate and ice with Dream Whip that was set aside.

title: cherry delight(moose's favorite)
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Add cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Put milk in a bowl along with lemon juice.
Stir well.
Add fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill for several hours (overnight is best).

title: fresh broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cut rice according to directions; set aside.
Saute onions in butter, using large saucepan.
Add the can of Cheddar cheese soup and stir.
Cut other cheese in and add to soup mixture; mix until all is melted.
Add mushrooms, juice and all.
Drain broccoli.
Add it with rice to the mixture and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Place onion rings on top or mix them in the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or longer.

title: cube steak surprise
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: hot crab and artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in quiche dish or other baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with French bread rounds, crackers or carrot sticks.

title: stir-fried zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini diagonally into 1/4-inch pieces.
In 5-quart Dutch oven or 10-inch skillet, over high heat in very hot salad oil, cook zucchini, stirring quickly and constantly, until well coated with oil.
Add salt, sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Reduce heat to medium-high; continue stir-frying 7 to 8 minutes until tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: braised beef
directions: Coat beef cubes with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot Wesson oil.
Add celery and onion; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, including remaining seasoned flour; stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with hot noodles, rice or mashed potatoes. Serves 4.

title: baked chicken with rice(luncheon dish - special)
directions: Do not use salt, as the soup is salty.

title: "puppy chow" snack
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Pour over the cereal (in a large bowl) and stir until coated.
Pour cereal into a large paper bag.
Sift confectioners sugar over this and shake bag.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 12 cups.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheet before transferring to wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all well.
Use 1/3 cup per cup hot water.

title: sausage macaroni skillet
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; set aside.
In a skillet cook sausage and green pepper until sausage is browned and pepper is tender; stir occasionally to break sausage into bits.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, pizza sauce and salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir in zucchini.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Stir in macaroni.
Cook uncovered for 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach out and squeeze all the water out.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
This goes great in middle of round loaf of brown bread.
Serve with crackers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry ground beef mixed with onion, salt and pepper until done. Drain grease.
Add peas, carrots and cooking wine.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Fix mashed potatoes, approximately 2 cups (fresh or instant).
Spread meat mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and cover with mashed potatoes and top with grated cheese.
Heat in microwave or 350° in conventional oven for 30 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil. Add carrots. Add flour, a little at a time, then rest of ingredients. Pour into two round pans, greased and floured. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: simple punch
directions: Thaw
sherbet
slightly.
Put
into punch bowl and pour the ginger ale over top of sherbet.

title: berry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and pour into a 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: melting moments
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add butter. Form into one-inch balls and flatten with fork. Bake at 300° for 20-25 minutes. Do not overbake. Makes 24 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix butter and soups together.
Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Add chicken, cooked egg noodles and mixed vegetables.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in cream cheese until fairly well mixed.
Add other ingredients.
Beat mixture until well blended.
Mold and chill until set.

title: spicy wiener snacks(microwave)
directions: Mix together in a glass dish.
Microwave 8 to 9 minutes, stirring often so they will cook evenly.
Serve with toothpicks. Good hot or cold.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries.
Fold in berries. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot-pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
In another bowl, stir pineapple, yogurt, eggs, liquid Butter Buds and vanilla.
Stir in sugar until blended.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened. Stir in carrots and raisins.
Spoon batter into muffin cups, lined with paper and sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Yield:
24 muffins.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Add baking powder, soda and salt to flour, then sift into a bowl. Add raisins to mixture.
Mix beaten eggs, melted butter and buttermilk to mixture and mix.
Grease and flour a baking pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Check with knife.
If it comes out clean, the loaf is done. Remove from oven and apply a small amount of butter to top of loaf to soften crust. Wrap in foil to keep fresh.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower, onion, broccoli and cucumber.
Mix together remaining ingredients and chill.

title: cornmeal breadsticks
directions: In a large bowl combine 1 cup flour, 1 cup cornmeal, sugar, salt and yeast. Blend.

title: tokay grape salad
directions: Mix sugar and vanilla into whipped cream.
Add remaining ingredients except Grape-Nuts; pour into mold or dish. Refrigerate.
Add Grape-Nuts just before serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Put in jar or jars.
You can keep in refrigerator for 3 months.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel peaches.
Place peach halves in pie shell until full. Mix sugar, butter, flour, egg and vanilla.
Pour over peach halves and bake at 375° until crust is brown, about 35 minutes.

title: english "fly" pie
directions: Mix flour with margarine and lard until consistency of bread crumbs.
Add 1 or 2 teaspoons cold water.
Mix into stiff dough. Roll out to form pastry base.
Bake base at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chunky crab salad
directions: Mix and handle crabmeat as little as possible.
Mix all dressing in a separate bowl.
Toss just enough to coat crab. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Bake patty shells according to package directions.
Heat soup with milk; add shrimp and peas and continue to heat, stirring until just simmering.
Cook slowly about 5 minutes.
Stir in the sherry and 1/2 the cheese (sprinkle remaining cheese in baked patty shells).
To serve, spoon shrimp into patty shells.
Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Starting with the lettuce, layer ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening or oil; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Serve with rice.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Place in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Stir, seal and keep in refrigerator.

title: 4 bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onions.
Add all beans with juices, ketchup, salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 375° without lid or slow cook on stove top.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In plastic bag, combine potato flakes, pepper and poultry seasoning.
In shallow bowl, combine egg whites and lemon juice.
Dip chicken, a few pieces at a time, in egg mixture.
Shake chicken in potato flake mixture to coat.
Place chicken in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Makes 4 to 5 servings. Calories per serving:
Dietary Exchanges:
1/2 starch; 3 lean meat.

title: special slaw
directions: In a bowl, combine cabbage and onion.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour buttermilk over cabbage mixture.
Toss to combine.
Cover bowl with plastic; refrigerate for several hours.

title: lithuanian kugel(potato pudding)
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Pour cool bacon and bacon fat over grated potatoes and onion.
Add beaten eggs and the rest of ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: irish stew(celtic)
directions: Cover lamb with boiling water and simmer for 1 hour, covered. Add carrots, celery, turnips, cubed potatoes, onion and seasonings. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add sliced potatoes, simmer another 30 minutes.
Serve with crusty bread.
Yields 4 servings.

title: "crock-pot" beef stew
directions: Empty into crock pot:
tomato soup, cream of celery soup, 1 can water, beef stew and Lipton onion soup mix.
Cut up carrots into 2 to 3-inch round slices and cut up potatoes as desired.
Add this to crock-pot.
Salt and pepper as directed.
Let cook on low all day.

title: english muffin hors d'oeuvres
directions: Drain bacon on paper towel and crumble up.
Mix bacon, olives, scallions and cheese with mayonnaise until creamy.
Cut toasted English muffins into quarters.
Spread about 1 teaspoon on each piece of muffin and broil until bubbly.
Serve hot for best taste. Mixture can be frozen until ready to use.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Combine flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Beat margarine for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat well. Stir dry ingredients gradually into beaten mixture, stirring until well blended. In a saucepan, heat together milk, chocolate pieces, 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt over low heat, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in walnuts and remaining vanilla. Pat 2/3 of oat mixture in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish. Spread chocolate over dough. Dot with remaining oat mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: In medium sauce pan, combine jello and crushed pineapple. Bring to boil, then remove from heat and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate until completely cool.

title: cherry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and refrigerate until all is eaten.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Measure the dry ingredients and sift them together.
Dice the bananas and add them to the dry ingredients along with the oil, vanilla, eggs and crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir to blend, but do not beat.

title: supreme zucchini cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar, then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and enough zucchini to mix easy.
Remove from mixer. Add remaining zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan (do not use oil sprays).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: health relish
directions: Grind peppers, cabbage, carrots and onions.
Add celery seed, mustard, vinegar, sugar and salt; mix well.
Let set for 2 hours; jar.

title: party cake
directions: Mix and bake the cake mix according to directions on box. Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix the pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread 1 large can of drained pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread cool whip over pineapple. Sprinkle coconut on top of cool whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot relish
directions: Add onions, carrots, peppers, cabbage and salt.
Let stand 2 hours and drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Stir all together.
Seal cold.

title: chinese salad
directions: Let stand.
But shake or mix well.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook and
crumble
sausage over medium heat until done. Drain on	paper
towels.	Cut
bread
into
1/4-inch cubes and place in bottom
of	greased
x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs.	Add milk to beaten eggs until mixed.
Combine sausage, mustard, salt and
cheese and stir in egg mixture.
Pour over bread cubes and refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.	Serves 8 to 10.

title: smooth perfect white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Salt and pepper to taste or add in cubed Velveeta cheese for a delicious cheese sauce.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with sugar and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Serves 50.

title: fish delight
directions: Place fillets in greased casserole dish. Mix soy sauce and lemon juice. Pour over fish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and then place under broiler and broil 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a bowl, mix together all except apples.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy, Proverbs 23:14. Bake in last two words of Mark 8:14. Serve with last clause of Galatians 5:13 to last seven works of Matthew 5:15. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. If you prefer, batter may be dropped by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and baked at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: cream soup
directions: Melt butter in soup kettle; add flour and salt to form a paste. Add milk. Stir until slightly thick. Add chicken broth, onion, potatoes, cauliflower and/or broccoli and celery. Simmer until vegetables are soft/firm.

title: mom's cheese casserole(good brunch item)
directions: Mix milk, eggs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Alternate layers of bread, cheese, chillies and meat in casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Add egg mixture.
Top with melted butter.
Refrigerate overnight, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Mix all of the above together. Make sure and tear the chicken into small bite size pieces. Add salt and pepper to taste. "Delicious".

title: microwave butterfinger bites
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave safe bowl stirring constantly. Pour crackers into melted chocolate and mix gently.
Spoon onto wax paper and serve when cool.

title: crispy crust chicken pie
directions: Debone and cut up chicken in bite size pieces; place in baking dish.
Mix the broth and celery soup.
Heat until smooth; pour over chicken.
Combine oleo, pepper, flour and milk and pour over all.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Pierce meat.
Pour marinade over steak and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: shirley's spoon bread
directions: Add first three ingredients to the hot milk.
Stir until smooth.
Combine well beaten eggs to buttermilk.
Add to hot milk mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in dish or pan which contains about 1/2 cup oil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey or roast beef burritos
directions: Warm together sour cream, mushroom soup, green chilies, 1/2 package of Cheddar cheese and turkey.
Bring to boil.
Put into burrito shells.
Roll and place in baking pan.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kugel (jewish noodle pudding)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well. Put in a greased pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve as side dish, dessert or breakfast dish.

title: ann's hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar and let stand overnight. Beat the egg and add sugar. Mix well with mustard and cook until boiling and thick.

title: honey granola
directions: Bring to boil the honey, butter, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Pour over oats, nuts and raisins. Mix and spread in a lightly greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Stir every 5 minutes. Cool and crumble. Store in airtight container for 2 weeks.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into pieces. Put 1/2 in bottom of buttered baking dish. Add raisins and rest of bread. Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour and milk. Mix well. Pour over bread. Let stand 1 hour and then bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with a sauce, if desired.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chip bacon and onions; fry until brown.
Put potatoes, bacon and onions in a kettle.
Cover with just enough water to cook potatoes and clams.
When done, add clam liquid, milk and seasonings.
If a thick chowder is desired, make a paste of melted butter and flour and thicken to desired consistency.
Add butter, salt and pepper.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Beat butter to a cream.
Add 1 cup of the sugar, then add cocoa; beat well.
Add coffee.
Add vanilla and second cup of sugar.
Beat well.

title: oven french toast
directions: Put butter, sugar and corn syrup in saucepan and bring to boil, stirring until syrupy.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Pour syrupy mixture on cookie sheet and cover bottom.
Layer bread 2 high across pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour over bread, making sure all bread is covered.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
When removing from pan, flip bread from bottom to top. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla on medium speed until fluffy. Add flour and finely chopped nuts.
Beat on low speed just until blended.
Chill dough.
Unwrap candies.
Preheat oven to 375°. Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy and form into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until cookies are set but not browned.
Cool slightly before rolling in powdered sugar.
Cool and store airtight.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Lightly mix beef, eggs, deviled ham, bread crumbs, salt, dry mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Shape into meatballs about 3/4-inch in diameter.

title: ? chicken ?
directions: Wash and sprinkle with salt, pepper and sweet basil.
Dip in flour.
Dip in milk.
Mix together equal parts of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip pieces of chicken in mixture.
Fry until golden brown in butter, oil and garlic cloves.
Put on cookie sheet pan (pan with sides) and bake for 15 minutes only at 375°.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Place sugar, rice, milk, water and dash of salt in 3-quart pan;
cook until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Set aside 1/2 can chow mein noodles.
Combine all ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a medium size bowl with an electric mixer, beat yolks and condensed milk at medium speed until pale and frothy.
Continue beating while slowly adding the lime juice in a thin stream.
Pour mixture into prepared pie shell.
In a clean, dry bowl, whip egg whites at low speed until frothy; increase speed to high and add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition.
When meringue is stiff, white and glossy, spread it over the pie filling, making sure edge of crust is covered.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Chill in refrigerator about 6 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put sherbet and vanilla ice cream in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up a little at a time until ice cream is mixed enough to drink.
(Don't mix too much 7-Up.
It will be too thin.)

title: bachelor pie
directions: Melt butter in a casserole or shallow dish.
Mix together sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour on top of melted butter; do not mix.
Spoon pie filling on top of batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or more.

title: kim's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add Ragu.
Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Start with macaroni and layer ingredients in baking dish.
Pour in meat mixture.
Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Cover with pepperoni.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: green onion and apple sausage
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Form into desired sized patties and fry over low to moderate heat until no longer pink in center. Careful--they burn easily if heat is too high!
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in low oven until the rest of the brunch is ready.
Yield:
12-15 patties.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine in microwave for 1 minute on 50% power.
Add all other ingredients and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat sauce; pour over carrots.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken with dumplings
directions: In large pot, combine chicken pieces, onion, carrots, celery, chicken broth, salt, bay leaves, pepper, thyme and 3 cups water. Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 35 minutes, until chicken and vegetables are tender.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken and vegetables.
Bring liquid to a boil (should be 5 to 6 cups).
Blend flour and 1/2 cup water until smooth; pour into boiling broth, stirring constantly until broth thickens.
Return chicken and vegetables to pot; bring to boil.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and cut each layer in half, making four layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Save 1 cup and mix with Cool Whip to ice top and sides.
Put first mixture between layers.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: sandy's mexican dip
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Add taco seasoning to ground meat. Layer beef on bottom of casserole. Combine softened cream cheese and sour cream. Spread cheese mixture on top of meat. Sprinkle with chopped green pepper and onion. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and olives. Bake at 350° until warm and cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook together onion soup, spaghetti and boiling water.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano and salt. Combine meat sauce to spaghetti and cook until right consistency.

title: pear honey
directions: Bring to a boil; boil for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with pineapple and juice. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over mixture of fruits, but do not stir.
Cover evenly with melted butter and sprinkle with nuts (as many as you like). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl. Stir in beaten egg whites and almond extract until well blended. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown. Remove right away from cookie sheet to wire racks. Cool completely. Dip cookies halfway into melted chocolate and put on wax paper to cool for 30 minutes or until firm. Makes about 3 dozen cookies. Store in airtight container up to 1 week.

title: no bake cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in cool whip by hand until smooth (no lumps).
Pour into crust, garnish with fruit.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, mix and cool.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add flour, salt, vanilla, nuts and chips.
The dough will be stiff.
Spread in large pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: spanish spice cake
directions: In large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Remove 3/4 cup of crumbly mix to use on top of cake.
Add the remaining 4 ingredients.
Pour cake batter in greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Top with 3/4 cup crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked holiday corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Place in well-greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Beat eggs well. Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder, then add alternately with milk to mixture.
Add all five flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian chicken bake
directions: Rub the outside of chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine melted margarine and garlic powder; set aside. Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, oregano, thyme and savory together until completely mixed.
Brush each piece of chicken with garlic-margarine mixture, then dip pieces in the seasoned bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve piping hot.

title: mexican rice and bean pie
directions: Warm pinto beans slowly with cumin, stirring occasionally. Mix rice with onion, jalapeno peppers and beaten egg.
Use back of a spoon to spread rice mixture into a 9-inch pan to make a "crust".
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Drain pinto beans and add this as next layer.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven for another 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: philly beef sandwiches
directions: Cook and stir onions in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Place bottom half of buns on ungreased cookie sheet. Top with onions and beef.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Place 4 halves on each sandwich.
Broil with tops, 5 to 6-inches from heat, until cheese melts.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: black forest cheesecake delight(yield: 10 servings)
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate malt bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, stir flour and baking powder together. In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add the egg, malted milk powder, milk and vanilla. Beat for 2 to 3 minutes until thoroughly combined, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally.
With the mixer on low, gradually add the flour mixture to the margarine mixture, beating for 2 or 3 minutes until thoroughly combined.
Fold in the 1 cup malted milk balls.
Spread into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
If desired, frost cooled bars with Quick Fudge Frosting and sprinkle with 1/3 cup of milk balls.
Makes 16 bars.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Great with raw veggies.

title: ore-ida au gratin
directions: Blend together in order.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch or 2 small casseroles.
Sprinkle potato chips on top and bake 1 hour at 350°. Can be made several hours ahead and refrigerated until baking time.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease clean potatoes and place in oven to bake 35 minutes.
Butter a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Peel and slice potatoes lengthwise and place a layer in the dish.
Sprinkle half of the brown sugar over this and dot with half of the butter. Over this, put half of the orange slices.
Add another layer of sliced potatoes and remaining butter, sugar and orange slices. Pour water over the top and lightly sprinkle with nutmeg and salt. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hurley gurley cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and cream cheese together and beat until smooth.
Combine 1 egg with the cake mix and butter until the dough forms a ball (stiff).
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Top with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Cool overnight and then cut in small pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Place crushed pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over the crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle the yellow cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Slice the butter and lay over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with whip cream.

title: no bake chocolate clusters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large pot.
After it begins to boil, only let it boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir.
Have the last 3 ingredients ready when the first comes from stove.
Mix quickly and drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased plate.
Use butter to grease the pan.
It hardens quickly, so work fast.

title: grandmother's coconut pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Stir together.
Heat until jelly melts.
Bake meatballs until heated.
Drain grease off on paper towel.
Add to sauce and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fish fry
directions: Cut fish into 3 x 3-inch pieces and dip into mixture of above and fry until golden brown.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, boil until almost done potatoes, celery and onion.
Drain and return to Dutch oven.
Add enough milk to cover vegetables, plus 1/2-inch.
Add ham, margarine and spices.
Simmer until potatoes are tender and almost ready to flake apart.
May be made thicker with cornstarch/water or flour/water if desired.

title: quick peanut cookies
directions: Melt margarine. Beat with sugar, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs. Combine flour, bran, oatmeal and soda. Mix well and stir into batter mix. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Place chicken in separate pieces of foil.
Top each piece with mushrooms, bay leaf and celery.
Dot with margarine.
Seal foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Don't drain pineapple.
In large bowl add cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix real well.
Fold in all of the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Simmer tomato juice with the sugar, minced onion, salt and celery salt 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes to the hot tomato mixture.
Pour over the soaked gelatin and stir until the gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Add lemon juice and Tabasco sauce and cool the mixture.
Add the chopped shrimp. Turn into a tray and freeze.

title: mrs. smith's coconut cake filling
directions: Mix, but do not stir, first 2 ingredients.
Place on stove and cook just enough to form a soft ball in water, or puts off big puffs of steam.
Take off of stove and add vanilla.

title: ranch pudding with whipped cream
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of chopped nuts and raisins on the bottom of pan.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, eggs, whiskey, melted butter, vanilla and salt in bowl and blend well.
Pour over nuts and raisins.
Arrange nut halves on top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with flavored whipped cream.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with an electric mixer.
Divide into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: green mixed burrito
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and cook slowly for about 30 minutes.
Add refried beans and mix well; cook 10 to 20 minutes more.
Remove wrapping from flour tortillas and wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until soft and pliable.
Place 1 or 2 tablespoons bean and meat mixture on one side of a flour tortilla and roll up in flute shape.
Keep warm until ready to eat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, water, raisins, shortening, salt, spices and nuts in saucepan.
Boil 10 minutes and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for ten minutes.

title: pokies gelatin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well; add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; alternately add flour mixture and milk to beaten mixture.
Pour into pan; bake 30 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Beat egg white and cream of tartar until stiff (not dry). Gradually add sugar, crackers and nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Spread the Dream Whip over the top.
Over top of that, add pineapple pie filling.
Chill and serve.
Can use any prepared pie filling in place of the pineapple.

title: peanut butter haystacks
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, and butter in saucepan and bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butt and corn flakes.
Dip out on wax paper to cool.

title: one dish meal
directions: Note:
Any meat may be substituted for chicken.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Put chocolate chips in blender.
Add hot coffee and liqueur and dash of salt.
Blend until chocolate is melted.
Add eggs. Blend.
Pour chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Blend thoroughly.
It will be soupy.
Pour into pie shell.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours. Top with whipped cream or topping.

title: sanders hot fudge sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add 1 cup hot water and bring to a boil, stirring often, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Keep in refrigerator.
Warm in microwave.

title: chicken perleau
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "philippine" tuna noodle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add the noodles, mushroom soup, nuts and tuna, mixing thoroughly.
Transfer into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together cheese, bread crumbs and the remaining margarine, melted.
Sprinkle this over the top of the tuna mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients except 3 eggs and put in greased 9-inch round dish.
Beat 3 eggs.
Pour on top of mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Mix all together and put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mocha swirl cheesecake
directions: Measure out 1/2 cup of the cake mix and set aside.
Place the remaining cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg in large mixing bowl. Blend with mixer until batter comes together in a ball.
Pat out the crust into a greased 9 x 13 pan, allowing the crust to come up 1/2 to 1-inch on the sides of the pan.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt and brown butter in 12 x 16-inch pan.
Mix lightly with beater the milk and eggs, then add sugar, salt and flour.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 23 minutes.
Serve hot with maple syrup, jelly or butter.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Place potatoes in large kettle.
Cover with water; add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender.
Drain and mash until smooth. In a saucepan, cook and stir butter, cheese, milk and remaining salt until smooth.
Stir into potatoes.
Fold in eggs.
Pour into a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
Sprinkle with chives. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk; mix well.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly a few times.
Roll to a 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon-custard bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Process all ingredients, except the egg whites (bread reduced to crumbs). Beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted.

Pour bread mixture onto beaten whites and carefully stir (fold) until no white clumps remain. Pour mixture into baking dish. Place dish in pan. Add hot water to pan to come halfway up sides of baking dish. Bake 55 to 65 minutes until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Remove from water to a rack. Serve warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Mix chicken with soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and sauteed mixture.
Drain spaghetti; put on bottom of baking dish and cover with chicken mixture.
Put grated cheese on top and bake until bubbly at 350° in oven or until light brown.

title: taco bake
directions: Spread crescent roll on cookie sheet (might need 2).
Bake according to directions.
Mix together browned ground beef, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Heat thoroughly.
Spread on prepared crust.
Top with shredded cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese. Top with lettuce, tomato, green pepper and onion.
Can add taco sauce or hot peppers to taste.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Add salt, pepper and water. Boil on medium heat, about 10 minutes. While heating potatoes, mix egg, salt, pepper and flour until you have a stiff dough. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon into boiling potatoes. Continue boiling until potatoes are tender. Add milk and margarine and more salt and pepper if needed. Cook until milk is hot.

title: chicken enchiladas 1
directions: Mix tomatoes and seasonings.
Dip tortillas in warm water to soften.
Layer: Put chicken in middle of tortilla, then add sauce mixture, add cheese.
Wrap tortilla and place in pan.
Cover tortillas in extra sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: tuna bake
directions: Beat bread crumbs, eggs and milk together.
Cook celery and onion in 1/2 cup water and chicken bouillon until tender.
Spread tuna in Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle vegetable mixture over tuna.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Bake until golden brown.

title: pasta with clam sauce
directions: In skillet, heat butter; add garlic and saute for 3 to 4 minutes or until garlic is golden.
Add clam juice and continue cooking until sauce is reduced in half.
Add clams and parsley. Continue cooking until heated through.
Toss pasta into sauce and continue to heat.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8 as a first course or 4 as a main course.

title: white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine orange juice and sugar; pour over hot cake and let cool.
Place cooled cake in refrigerator overnight before removing from pan.
It may be frozen also.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice bake
directions: Saute celery and onion in melted butter in saucepan until tender (do not brown).
Combine soup, water and cheese spread. Add to saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine hot cheese mixture with cooked rice.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt.
Melt margarine in baking dish (flat) and add corn mixture. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add buttermilk all at once. Mix and add flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Add last the boiling water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and add sugar. Beat egg yolks. Add to butter and sugar.
Add flour (baking powder sifted in) and 1 tablespoon sweet milk (cream is better).
Fold in egg whites (beaten stiff). Add flavoring.

title: one pie crust made in pan
directions: Melt water and Crisco together.
Mix ingredients into pie plate.
Pat out to edge of pan.

title: taco dip
directions: On a platter, make layers: 1st layer is refried beans.
2nd layer, combine sour cream, mayo and taco mix.
Pour over refried beans.
3rd layer, put sliced vegetables. 4th layer, add taco sauce and cheddar cheese.

title: almond praline sauce
directions: Combine marshmallows, brown sugar and half and half in a large saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in almonds just before serving.
(This is a yummy sauce that can be used over ice cream or to jazz up a bought cheesecake.)

title: baked chicken crescents
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Spray a long deep baking dish (use a nonstick spray).
Break chicken up into pieces.
Place chicken pieces along with crescent rolls.
Add strips of thinly sliced cheese and roll one at a time.
Place in a baking dish.
Heat only to mix
soup and milk.
Pour over rolls and bake 25 minutes at 350° or until slightly browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes to soft ball.
Stir constantly.
Good ice cream topping.

title: short-cut lasagne
directions: In large skillet, brown meat; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce, seasonings and water and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese and egg; mix well.
In bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread 1 cup of the hot mixture.
Cover with 3 noodles; then another cup of sauce, 1/3 of the cheese mix, 1/3 of the shredded Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of the Parmesan.
Then repeat, ending with sauce and cheese on top.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until cheese is melted and noodles are tender. May also be baked the same day.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the buttermilk.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk mixture, mixing well.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook linguine according to package directions; keep warm.
Cook garlic in butter and wine in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add shrimp and cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, until shrimp turns pink.
Add salt and pepper and spoon mixture over hot linguine.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately. Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute oleo and onion until onion is tender.
Add broccoli (cooked according to package directions).
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Pour into well buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° until it comes to a bubbly boil.

title: california tarts
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Make small balls; place in small muffin tin.
With your finger, press crust until bottom and sides are covered.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese in saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Combine confectioners sugar and cocoa together.
Add to cheese mixture, stirring to blend.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Pour into a 10 x 14-inch glass dish.
Chill in refrigerator. Cut into 25 squares to serve.

title: david's playschool candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add cornflakes and mix until all flakes are coated.
Spoon on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Refrigerate.
Candy will be done after you read two stories.

title: chili dip
directions: Saute onion; remove and cook meat; drain meat.
Add chili and simmer 10 minutes.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces; add cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
You can keep dip warm in crock-pot and serve with chips or whatever you prefer.

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, place chicken.
Top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato. Combine margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: lemon chicken(serves 2)
directions: Lay breasts in Pyrex dish.
Put crushed garlic over this, then a sprinkling of garlic powder and pepper.
Blend lemon juice plus rind (put all or part of rind in food processor) plus water together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover chicken entirely with Progresso seasoned Italian bread crumbs.
Then chopped parsley. Drizzle with olive oil over the top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven uncovered.

title: dinner roll coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Layer dinner rolls evenly around pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar.
Pour melted margarine over other ingredients.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Let stand for 8 hours or overnight at room temperature.
Place foil on wax paper underneath to catch any droppings.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Invert onto plate.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of water.
Add to apple juice and cinnamon.
Cook slowly until sauce is
clear.
Put apples in pie shell and pour apple juice over them.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until apple are done.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Strain the liquor into the gelatin.
Add the vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cool.
If desired, add the walnuts and olives.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: blueberry bread
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll thawed dough out to fit a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Beat cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Spread over bread dough. Sprinkle with blueberries.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar in a small bowl. Cut in margarine or butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over blueberries.
Let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes or until puffy.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Cool. Drizzle with glaze, if desired.

title: aunt ida's society cheese
directions: Put first three ingredients through meat grinder.
Add mayonnaise to make soft mixture, like cream cheese, that will spread easily.
Delicious on a variety of crackers.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Add first 7 ingredients together in medium saucepan.
Cook until cranberries pop and split.
Add last 3 ingredients and simmer all together for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and red bell pepper salad
directions: Whisk together the mayonnaise and vinegar to make the dressing. Toss the broccoli, bell peppers, onions, bacon and nuts in a large bowl. Add dressing and toss gain.
Season with salt and pepper.
The salad will keep in the refrigerator for a day or two.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Dissolve soda
in buttermilk; add with flour and spices to cream mixture.
Mix 1 cup flour with fruit.
Add to batter.
Beat egg whites stiff and add to mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: pickled squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onion and salt; mix well.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain well.
Mix peppers, squash, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Add mixture to drained squash; bring to a boil. Pack in jars and seal.
Do not use aluminum pan.
Granite is best.

title: beef or deer stir-fry
directions: In skillet, heat deer or beef; let boil for 15 minutes.
May need to add water 1/2 cup to 1 cup.
Use enough liquid to keep from boiling dry but don't make it too soupy because the frozen vegetables will have their own liquid.
Add 4 or 5 shakes of Worcestershire sauce.
Turn down heat to low; add vegetables. Cook until vegetables are cooked yet still slightly crunchy. Serve over rice with soy sauce.

title: persimmons pudding cake
directions: Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan on 325° for 45 minutes.

title: thursday night friends favorite chili
directions: In a large saucepan, brown the ground beef, or warm the veggie crumbles with the chopped onions.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve topped with grated cheddar cheese and sour cream, optional.

title: baked bananas(makes one)
directions: Slice banana in half lengthwise and put into an ovenproof dish.
Pour on the maple syrup.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon and dot with butter. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crispy cheese squares
directions: In bowl combine butter with cheese.
Blend in flour and cayenne pepper.
Mix in cereal.
Press into a buttered 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until crisp.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: homemade noodle soup
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 teaspoon thyme and salt in bowl. Beat egg yolk with 3 tablespoons water in another small bowl; add to flour mixture.

Stir until well blended. Shape into ball. Place dough on lightly floured surface; flatten. Knead about 5 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic, adding more flour if necessary. Wrap dough in plastic; let stand 15 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Boil noodles.
Mix sauces together.
Put ground beef in large baking dish after draining it.
Mix in noodles, then sauces.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: reba's surprise
directions: Use turkey, chicken or ham.
Set oven at 350°.
Mix all the ingredients and put on meat; cook for as long as it takes to cook meat.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix and sift flour, soda and salt.
In separate bowl, cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars gradually; cream until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
Using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each cookie, shape into balls and roll in the 1/4 cup white sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; press an unwrapped candy kiss on each cookie.
Press down firmly so that the cookie cracks around the edges, then return to oven and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer. Remove; let cool.

title: hot tamales
directions: Combine onions, salt, garlic, chili quick, chili powder, water, Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce, jalapeno peppers and powdered cumin in blender.
After blending, pour into mixture of ground beef, ground pork and corn meal.
Combine both meat mixture and blended mixture thoroughly.
Let stand a few minutes.

title: fowl play
directions: Cover bottom of a deep 2 1/2-quart casserole with broccoli. Layer remaining ingredients (onion slices, breasts, salt and pepper, mushrooms, bacon, cheese and sherry) over broccoli.
Cover casserole with foil and bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil, reduce temperature to 375° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip. Line pan with graham crackers. Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers; add 2nd layer of crackers and add remaining mixture.

title: american pizza
directions: Prepare hot roll mix by direction for pizza dough.
Make 2 crusts.
Pour desired amount of sauce on each crust.
Same with hamburger and remaining topping.
Always end with cheeses.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 25 minutes or until crust edge is deep golden brown. My kids have fun creating their own pizza.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Heat soup and milk.
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Bake 45 minutes.
Add extra cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: basil-tomato pie
directions: Prebake pie crust according to directions.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Cool on a wire rack. Cut tomatoes into wedges; drain on paper towels.
Arrange wedges atop melted cheese in pie shell.
In a food processor bowl, combine basil and garlic; cover and process.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Day before cooking, mix yeast and lukewarm water.
Set aside to dissolve.
In very large mixing bowl, pour boiling water over Crisco, stirring until dissolved.
Let cool enough to add eggs and yeast mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator several hours before cooking and let rise in a warm place.
About 3 hours before cooking, knead dough lightly; roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip rolls in melted butter before placing in muffin pan.
Let rise until doubled in size (about 2 hours).
Cook at 375° until brown.

title: easy pecan turtles
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add milk and caramels; keep over boiling water until well blended.
Add 2 cups pecans. Drop on wax paper.
Cool in freezer until ready to dip into chocolate.

title: french crepes
directions: Mix flour and salt in large bowl.
Make a well in center and add eggs, melted butter and half of milk.
With a whisk or wooden spoon, gradually stir the flour into the liquid mixture.
While stirring, gradually add more liquid until consistency is that of cream.
When all liquid is added, beat or whisk to remove all lumps.
Pour 1/4 cup of crepe batter into preheated pan.
Cook both sides on low heat until lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 crepes. Fill with fruit, ice cream, or scrambled eggs.
Fold and enjoy.

title: oatmeal raspberry bars
directions: Combine oleo and brown sugar until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, except preserves (mixture will be dry).
Place 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Press into pan and spread preserves over. Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: no-cook dill pickles
directions: Place 2 stalks of dill in bottom of jar.
Wash cucumbers and pack them into jar.
Add salt, sugar, vinegar and 2 stalks of dill.
Fill to top with added water.
Seal.
Store in cool place at least 6 weeks before using.
Liquid may leak out of lid while pickles are working.
Do not disturb if this happens.

title: halloween treats(easy kid recipe)
directions: Heat together the sugar and milk in a 2-quart saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, then add vanilla and crackers.
Mix well.
Cool.
Form into 1-inch balls. Makes 34.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add liquid ingredients; mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix together oats, peanut butter, nonfat dry milk, honey, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Stir well until all blended.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, oleo and confectioners sugar together with a fork or	a pastry blender until crumbly.
Press into a greased and floured 9
x
13-inch
cake
pan.
Bake
for 20 minutes at 350°. Beat
eggs, sugar and lemon juice together with a mixer until well blended.
Pour
over
first
layer and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool
for
5 to 10 minutes and sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut while still hot.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into 40 small balls.
Place 20 at a time in a 9-inch glass pie dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, turning once until brown.

title: trojan woman
directions: In punch bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Place ice in bowl.
Add club soda to taste.
Garnish with chunks of orange sherbet and orange slices.
Yields 20 to 25 punch cups.

title: brownies
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients until melted.
Mix.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach ring
directions: Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over the beaten egg yolks.
Add salt and pepper.
Add spinach and grated onion, then cool.
Fold in the stiffly beaten whites of eggs.
Grease a ring pan well; set in a shallow pan of water to bake in a 350° oven.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Turn out carefully on a platter; fill the center with creamed eggs, mushrooms or carrots.
Serves 8.

title: favorite sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend yams with sugar, salt, spices, butter, cream and orange juice.
Cut 6 marshmallows in half and mix with yams.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Top with remaining marshmallows.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes or until mixture is puffy and marshmallows delicately browned.
Serves 6.
May be warmed in microwave
until hot.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased 10 inch pan.
Bake at 350 until brown about 30 minutes.

title: grandma's pork and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Put in large casserole dish or pan.
Cut bacon into small pieces and place
on top.
Bake in a 350° or 375° oven until bacon has browned.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Pour the first 5 ingredients into a buttered glass pie pan or baking dish. Cover with the peaches.
(I use halves and cut them. It always is the right amount.)
Top with the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Sprinkle an ample amount of sugar over the top and finally cinnamon. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: "french fried" onion rings
directions: Combine onion and milk.
Let stand 30 minutes, turning frequently.
On wax paper, combine bread crumbs, chili powder and salt.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray nonstick jelly roll pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Turn onion rings into bread crumb mixture to coat.
Place onion rings in pan; drizzle evenly with oil.
Bake for 5 minutes on each side.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Measure 1/2 cup warm water (110° to 115°) into mixing bowl. Add yeast, stirring to dissolve. Stir in 1 1/2 cups warm water, eggs, sugar, salt, shortening and flour. Beat until smooth (100 strokes). Cover and let rise until very light (1 hour). Beat down and pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Let rise to within 1-inch of top of pan (45 minutes). Bake until golden brown and crusty at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes. Servings: 16.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla, cocoa and potatoes. Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts and egg whites.
Pour into 2 prepared layer pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all the above and top with dill dip (see below).

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly and shape into 1/2 inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 18-20 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix frozen bags of coconut and pecans together.
Spread into greased pan.
Pat evenly with hands. Mix cake mix according to package and pour over coconut and nuts.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Have Kisses unwrapped before removing cookies from oven.

title: praline yams
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place drained yams in ungreased 1-quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Sprinkle over yams.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Drain.
Add garlic salt, oregano and cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon on sliced rye bread.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick with an electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: aunt cindy's holiday mold
directions: Make Jell-O using 3 cups water; jell slightly.
Add celery, nuts and pineapple.
Mash cranberry sauce and add to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased mold.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.

title: 4-layered marinated salad
directions: Place the lettuce in a 9 x 13-inch pan or large, round container about that size.

title: pea pot
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole and bake at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Saute carrots, peas and onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, tuna and milk in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add vegetable mixture.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Add noodles to casserole.
Mix well and bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Remove giblets.
Rinse chicken with cold water; pat dry. Sprinkle cavity and skin with salt and pepper; truss chicken. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon around chicken.
Cover with foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: crawfish pie
directions: In a skillet, saute crawfish tails in 1/2 stick butter for 10 minutes.
In another skillet, saute green onions and parsley in 1 stick butter.
Then blend in flour and gradually add cream, stirring constantly, to make a thick sauce.
Add sherry.
Blend crawfish tails to cream sauce being careful not to include fat in bottom of skillet.
Season with salt, black pepper and red pepper. Place mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Freezes well.
Serves 4.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar
and
milk.
Sift
2 cups of the flour,
salt
and
baking powder together.	Add to milk and egg mixture;
beat
batter (with beater, blender or food processor) until smooth,
adding
only
as
much
of the other 1 to 2 cups flour as
needed.
Batter should be thin enough to go through a funnel, but
not too runny.
Heat oil to 375° in an 8 or 9-inch skillet about
3/4 inch deep.
It is important to have and keep the oil hot.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Swirl and crisscross	batter	in oil in lace like pattern, keeping finger over
bottom
of
funnel until ready to drizzle batter into hot oil.
Let
cake
brown on one side, turn and brown on the other side; it
takes 1 minute or less to bake.
Lift from oil, place on plate and sprinkle with 10x sugar (or syrup, molasses, jelly or jam).
Yield
6 to 8 funnel cakes.	The frying can become an art, since
all	sorts
of
shapes
can be made with twists and turns of the funnel.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook first three ingredients for 8 minutes after boiling starts.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Stir until dissolved. Chill and cut.

title: cola fruit salad
directions: Stir 1 cup hot cola with Jell-O until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold cola.
Chill until slightly thickened, then stir in pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into individual molds or a ring mold, chill until firm.
Just use any container as you would for Jell-O salad. Serves 6 to 8 people!

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In a sauce pan combine sugar and vinegar, boil to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Add cooking oil and salt.
Pour over vegetables and marinate 24 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy pan.
Cook and stir until it pulls away from sides and follows spoon.
Turn out and knead.
If sticky, add flour.
Divide and add food coloring, if desired. Knead.
Store in Baggies.
Much better than store-bought play dough, as it does not get hard and is very pliable.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in a big bowl.
Pour into a 2-quart bowl or pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water; stir in sherbet until dissolved.
Mix in marshmallows and oranges.
Let set up about 3 hours in small square casserole dish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: julia's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and banana; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add them to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream and juice; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Blend together well.
Enjoy with apple slices, strawberries or any fruit.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 4 hours.

title: pat's shepherds pie
directions: In a med. bowl, stir potatoes, 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the onions.
Spoon into greased 1-1/2 qt. casserole dish, spread on bottom and up sides to make a shell.
In another bowl, combine chicken, vegetables, soup and seasonings.
Pour into potato shell. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook the rice, water and bouillon cubes about 35 minutes. Cook the chicken breasts or chicken until tender.
Remove chicken and cut in cubes.
To the broth, add the celery, onion and carrots. Cook until tender.
Combine all ingredients. Add the milk, soups and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and 3/4 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix in shredded carrots, zucchini, onion and yellow squash.
Mix melted margarine and stuffing mix.
Divide moist stuffing in half.
Spread first half of stuffing on the bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with vegetable mixture. Spread the remaining half of stuffing on top of vegetables, then sprinkle with remainder Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wellington
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Drain excess fat.
Add onion, mushrooms and broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is thawed.
Drain. Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until well blended. Roll out crescent rolls, spoon sausage mixture down middle.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Fold crescent roll over and seal.
Bake as directed on crescent roll package.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Cut marshmallows, pineapple and cherries into quarters. Combine with pecans and lemon juice in a bowl; mix well.
Combine egg yolks, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Cook until thickened to custard consistency, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold into fruit.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill, covered, for 24 hours.

title: mexican hot dog sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Mix and mash well with potato masher.
Cover and cook over very low flame for 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Mix all together in a casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Bake, covered, about 30 minutes and uncovered for the rest of the time.

title: dill pickles - deli style(makes 6 quarts)
directions: Bring brine ingredients to a boil.
Wash cukes and cut off ends.
Pack in quart jars.
Add dill and 3 cloves of garlic.
Pour boiled juice over until pickles are covered.
Screw cap on lids. Refrigerate 24 hours or more and eat after 4 days.
Keeps a month in refrigerator.
Recipe easily cuts in half for pickle supply.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter or margarine; beat together until fluffy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth; stir in vanilla.
Spread over cake; sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: creamy italian pasta
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: candied sweets
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Place a layer in bottom of buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and salt; dot with butter.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used, ending with sugar and butter.

title: spanish paella
directions: You will need a large cast-iron skillet.

title: dilled meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs and ketchup and form into 48 (1-inch) balls.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add meat balls, brown, then remove from pan.
Remove excess grease, all except for 2 tablespoons.
In remaining grease, blend in flour and celery salt. Cook until smooth.
Gradually stir in consomme.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes over low-medium heat until thick.
Add dill and meatballs. Serve hot with rice or buttered noodles.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour with soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
At low speed add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin.
Stir in morsels and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread into loaf pan.
Sprinkle with rest of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Let stand 6 hours before slicing.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on top of stove in 1/4 cup oil.
Place in baking dish and pour chicken noodle soup over pork chops.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with dill slices.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Stir together boiling water and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and freeze.
May be frozen in small individual serving containers, if desired.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Mix 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of water.
May be served hot or iced.
Makes about 80 to 100 cups.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Grind hamburger and veal or pork together.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Make in small balls and roll in flour.
Brown in Crisco and drain.

title: fudge cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat (do not boil).
Add pecans; stir until coated.
