In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and unbeaten eggs; mix until just blended.
Stir in chocolate and pecan mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring; do not beat. Fill paper cups in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Makes 16 cupcakes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Strain tomatoes.
Add an equal quantity of water.
Add onion, garlic, catsup, butter, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce. Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Season to taste.
Simmer 20 or 30 minutes more.
Thicken with flour, if desired, and cook until blended.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order, adding hot water last.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's lemon pie
directions: You will need a clean pot (lid is optional), desired amount of water and stove or heating unit as source of energy (use open fire for outdoor use only).

title: cherry-pineapple cobbler
directions: Mix together cherry, pineapple and sugar.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Cover with butter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat.

title: hot chili bean dip
directions: Place beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with beef, cooked with onion.
Cover with chilies and taco sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cover with sour cream and olives.
Use taco chips and dip away!

title: burger casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook celery and onion until tender. Stir to separate meat; pour off fat.
Add soup and salt.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole.
Mound potatoes around edge of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix 1 cup water, food coloring and oil. Pour into dry ingredients and mix.
Add rest of water and mix. Store in an airtight container.

title: easy onion dip
directions: Combine sour cream and soup mix together.
Mix well.
Ready to serve.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Stir apricots into boiling water; let cool.
Cream the brown sugar and shortening.
Stir in egg, flour, milk, soda and salt. Add apricots with water.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Drop by dessert spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cookies are moist, tasty and keep well.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cool, baked cake.
Layer half of cake crumbs in punch bowl.
Top with 1/2 each of pudding, pie filling, drained pineapple, banana and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers using remaining 1/2 of each of the ingredients.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.

title: shrimp beignets
directions: Boil water and butter.
Dump flour in all at once.
Stir until makes a ball and comes off the side.
Take away from heat and cool.
Put in one egg at a time.
Add shrimp; stir.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Drop, a teaspoon at a time, in hot grease.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Beat well.
Add sugar and add one egg at a time and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add lemon.
Beat well.
Flour raisins and fold in batter.
Bake at 325° in tube pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Put in baking dish and divide into 2 halves.
Top with tomato catsup and season with salt. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: asparagus chicken
directions: Cook, bone and skin chicken.
Partially cook asparagus.
Blend soup, mayonnaise, curry and garlic salt.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole pan.
Spread asparagus on bottom of pan.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter, crumbs and sugar.
Mix well. Press mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate morsels in microwave or double boiler and spread over the peanut butter mixture.
Chill 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and return to refrigerator.

title: orange sherbet dessert
directions: Remove and reserve pulp and juice from oranges. Mix sherbet, pulp and juice. Fill each half heaping with sherbet mixture; place in freezer. Before serving, top each orange with Cool Whip.

title: south of the border fettucini with grilled chicken and black beans
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter.
Add tomatoes, beans, cilantro leaves, jalapeno and garlic.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Add grilled chicken and wine; simmer. Add chicken stock and simmer until reduced by 1/4.
Salt and pepper.
Bring large pot of water to boiling.
Drop pasta (fettucini) in and cook 3 minutes.
Drain.
Top with sauce. Serves 2 to 4.

title: dutch baby
directions: Mix flour and eggs in bowl; add milk and mix.

title: fat-free potato wedges
directions: Note:
Buy 4 potatoes that way a scant 1 pound total.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, Miracle Whip and curry powder and pour over broccoli/chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes. Add cheese and bake until just melted.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Bring margarine and grated cheese to room temperature.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Make into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Garnish each with paprika.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp but not brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine ingredients except pie shell.
Heat and boil, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour into pie shell.
Top when cool with Cool Whip.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix both the regular and brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg. Spread 1/3 of apples in unbaked deep-dish pie crust. Spread 1/3 of filling on top. Repeat. Pour 1/4 cup milk in center and dot with margarine. Top with an unbaked crust. Brush crust with 1 tablespoon milk. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Spread pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Combine margarine and salt.
Pour over pecans, stirring well.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, and onion.
Add egg and gradually beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot grease in deep fryer. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Put Italian dressing in a bowl.
Add eggs, tomato and parsley and mix together.
Pour over salad.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine ingredients together in a heavy sauce pan over medium heat.
Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Serve over warm buttered biscuits and enjoy.

title: texas brownies
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add the eggs and sour cream and beat for 2 minutes.
Combine the margarine, water and cocoa in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Add to above mixture and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into an 11 x 12 x 1-inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oat bran - banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients, making a well in the center of the mixture.
Combine bananas and other 3 ingredients.

Also vanilla, if desired. Add this to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Coat muffin pan cups with nonstick spray and spoon batter until about 3/4 full. Yields 12 muffins. Bake about 15 minutes or until done.

title: corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Put
in
pan
and
melt
sticks
oleo.
Mix molasses, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Mix sugars, soda, salt, buttermilk
and
eggs.
Mix
the above together well.
Put 5 pounds
flour
in pan and make a hole and pour mixture in.
Mix and pat in hand and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick spray.
In blender, blend eggs until fluffy.
Add milk, baking mix and seasonings; blend well.
Place your favorite fillings in prepared pie plate. Pour egg mixture over this.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Use about 2 cups of filling per pie.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor, with metal blade or blender, combine all ingredients.
Cover; process 30 seconds (15 seconds in blender). Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir frequently.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl; put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: caramel cream pie
directions: Brown and drain pecans and coconut in margarine. Drain on a paper towel.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak. Cook onion and green pepper in fat until tender.
Brown meat in fat. Add tomatoes, juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and dice. Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to chicken and other ingredients. Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips. Bake in 9 x 12-inch casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy chicken creole
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in oil until onion is translucent. Add diced tomatoes, tomato paste, salsa, Worcestershire sauce, spices and sugar. Stir until blended and bubbling. Add diced chicken and cover. Simmer 40 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender. Serve on bed of rice with crackers and salad.

title: popsicles
directions: Add boiling water to jello, sugar and Kool-Aid.
Add cold water.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: the "holey" egg
directions: You will also need 1 small to medium water glass and 1 medium size skillet or frying pan.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream granulated sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well; set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add and blend into sugar-shortening mixture.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Form into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Freeze overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood-cucumber filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.
Double the recipe for a tea for 40 to 50.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss with diced cucumbers, tomatoes, red onions, cooked spaghetti, Italian salad dressing and Salad Supreme by McCormick. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.
Pour mixture into container of a 1 gallon freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer with additional ice and salt and let stand for 1 1/2 to 2 hours to ripen before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Wash and dry dried beef.
Cut beef into small pieces.
Add beef, chopped onion and Accent to cream cheese. Mix and form into a ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature.

title: golden vegetable soup
directions: Place vegetables in pan with just enough water to cover. Simmer until tender. Add milk. Mix cornstarch into water. Add slowly to soup. When heated through add cheese, stir until melted.

title: scampi
directions: Saute shrimp in hot oil; add vermouth, garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer until liquid is almost absorbed.
Sprinkle with parsley and lemon juice.
Stir gently to mix.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Measure first 7 ingredients into bowl and beat on medium speed about 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. Bake in two 9-inch pans (1 1/2 inches deep) or 10 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Less time for layers.
Frost with Chocolate Fudge Frosting.

title: cranberry relish bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Beat eggs, add liquid, orange rind and melted shortening.
Add all at once to flour mixture and stir until flour is just dampened.
Add cranberries and nuts, stir just enough to blend well.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool several hours or overnight before slicing.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Add marshmallows and beat well.
Cool (about an hour or so) until spreading consistency.
Delicious on Duncan Hines caramel cake or any chocolate or yellow cake.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Put stew meat and vegetables in large casserole. Mix soups and pour over meat and vegetables. Cover and bake in 325° oven for 3 hours. Meat will be brown and vegetables will remain whole. Serves 4.

title: easy lentil soup
directions: Boil all ingredients, then cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, until beans are tender.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Trim all visible fat from chops.
Use one piece of fat to lightly grease a nonstick frying pan.
Brown chops over medium-high heat on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add broth.
Cover. Reduce heat to low.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes, turning twice during this time.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until they are thoroughly mixed. Roll into small balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Put in roaster with rack for 1 hour, covered.
Drain grease; add sliced onions and remaining ingredients.
Bake in covered roaster at 350° for 1 hour, then uncovered for 1/2 hour more.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine water, sugar and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Let mixture boil slowly, uncovered, over low heat for five minutes.
Add maple flavoring.
Makes 2 cups.

title: enchiladas(chicken or turkey)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the chicken broth, chili powder, garlic salt, cumin and salt, and bring to a boil.
Stir together the cornstarch and water and mix until smooth; add to the broth. Stir together the chicken or turkey, olives, almonds, 1/2 c. cheddar, and 1/2 c. enchilada sauce.
Put remaining enchilada sauce in a small pan and heat.
Put
filling in a skillet with 2 Tbsp. butter or margarine and heat through.
Put oil in a small skillet and fry tortillas quickly on both sides.
Drain and keep warm in a covered dish.
Dip tortillas in heated enchilada sauce and lay in a 9 x 13 inch dish.
Put a spoonful of filling on across each one and roll tightly.
Place all side by side in the dish.
Sprinkle with 1 c. cheddar cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour remaining enchilada sauce over all.
Top with sour cream and green onions.
Serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In saucepan, add shortening, salt and 1 cup hot water.
Bring to a small boil just until Crisco melts.
Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons water.
Beat eggs, add 1/4 cup sugar to beaten eggs, add alternately with flour and shortening mixture, also yeast at this time.
Place in greased bowl, turning to coat all sides.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and bring to a boil. Cook to soft-ball stage (238° to 240°) on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Keep stirring until nuts no longer come to the top of the mixture. Quickly drop by spoonful on waxed paper. When cool, remove and store.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Jiffy mix.
Add Jiffy mix.
Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cream butter; add brown sugar and whip until fluffy.
In a large baking pan, combine popcorn.
Mix in creamed mixture.
Bake in 350° oven or about 8 minutes or until crisp.
Serve warm, if desired.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: easy sweet and sour sauce
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in buttered casserole (9 x 11-inch).
Make topping.

title: cherry delite (salad or dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine in extra large bowl and mix.

title: taco pie
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet until crumbly. Add taco sauce. Simmer for 15 minutes. Layer corn chips, ground beef and cheese in baking dish. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered kettle and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Makes 15 cups.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese puffs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and spread onto sliced French bread.
Broil in oven until puffy and golden brown, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix well and add 1 small can evaporated milk.
Blend well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Cook in large skillet over medium heat until browned; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except pineapple; mix well and pour over meatballs.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple; simmer an additional 10 minutes, stirring often.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.
(Freezes well.)

title: fast and easy mexican casserole
directions: Spray large casserole dish with pam.
Cover bottom with chips and crush with hand.
(about 1 in. thick) In a large pot on stove put water, onion, soup and rotel.
Microwave chicken until defrosted and place in pot (with juice).
Cook on med. for 5 min. Pour mixture over chips and top with cheese.
Bake at 400 for 15 min.
Serve with refried beans and Spanish rice.
Serves 4-6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients into a large casserole dish with a lid.
It helps to separate the cream cheese and mix throughout the frozen corn.
Cover and put in the oven to bake.
After 30 minutes remove lid and stir contents well.
Cover and continue to cook for 30 minutes.
Total cooking time is 1 hour.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, oil and corn in a mixing bowl; blend well and set aside.

Pour half of corn meal batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle with cheese. Saute ground beef until lightly browned; drain thoroughly. Crumble beef over cheese and sprinkle with onion and peppers. Pour remaining corn meal over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: ranch round steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; cut into serving size pieces. Slash edges to prevent curling.
Combine flour, dry mustard, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; use to coat meat.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen large cookies.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Line a 10-inch pizza pan with cookie dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool. Combine cream cheese and whipped topping in bowl; mix well. Spread over baked layer.

title: my mama's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place butter and put in oven until butter is melted.
Remove.
While butter is melting, mix together the flour, sugar and milk.
Peel and cut up fruit.
While butter is very hot, pour in liquid mixture.
Add fruit over batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours or until browned.

title: picadilla dip
directions: Marinate the ground round in the dry sherry in a roaster, adding the salt, pepper and jalapeno peppers, for 1 hour.
In a little oil, saute garlic, onions and green peppers.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and pimentos.
Simmer to right consistency.
Add to marinated meat.
Simmer until all is cooked and again right consistency.

title: oven round steak dinner
directions: Season meat with 2 teaspoons salt and dash of pepper. Roll in flour. Cook onions in hot fat until tender but not brown; remove onion and brown meat slowly on both sides. Place meat in 3-quart casserole; add onions, potatoes and bay leaf. Pour soup over. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Add beans; cook 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: the best hot 'n' spicy appetizer
directions: Saute chicken breasts in small amount of olive oil just until tender.
Chop chicken very fine.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and blend thoroughly with a fork or spatula.
Bake in flat dish (like a Pyrex pie pan) for 20 minutes at 375°.
Transfer hot dip to serving bowl.
Serve with Fritos Scoops, Triscuits or Tostitos.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in a covered container.
Will keep indefinitely. Pour 2 or 3 teaspoons into a cup of hot water.

title: sweet cucumber (or beet) pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, water and sugar together.
(Add spices to taste, if desired.)
Bring to a boil.
Add prepared cucumbers or beets and bring to a boil again.
Immediately remove from heat and pack into jars.
Add liquid mixture and seal.
(They will be nice and crisp.)

title: "oh boy" waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Mix eggs, milk and oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, beating only until moistened. Bake in preheated baker.
Makes 10 to 12 waffles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat egg, sugar and oil. Add zucchini and mix well. Add rest of ingredients; mix well. Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine until bubbly; add chicken and cook until browned on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms until liquid has evaporated; sprinkle with flour and stir to combine.
Gradually stir in water; add orange juice and broth mix and, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, add chicken and let simmer for about 3 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve sprinkled with scallions and topped with orange sections.
Makes
4 servings, 273 calories each.

title: rice dressing
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables for 10 minutes; add all other ingredients and pour over uncooked rice in an 8 x 12-inch pan. Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rosettes
directions: Add sugar to eggs.
Stir very gently.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Combine with the egg mixture, stirring gently, until all lumps are dissolved.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Dip in sugar while hot.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper.
Mix can of soup and cheeses in saucepan until cheeses are melted.
Add cans of hominy. Pour entire mixture into a casserole or baking dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter; cover and refrigerate. To serve, bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until hot.
Great when entertaining as it can be made the day before.

title: 4 step pie
directions: Mix and pat out in 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix sugars, vanilla, cream cheese, sour cream and nuts. Clean and remove stems from grapes (slice in half). Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: pepperoni omelet
directions: Slice pepperoni.
Put in 10-inch skillet.
Cook over low flame until fat melts.
Add Ricotta.
Let melt.
Beat eggs; add to pan. Let settle.
Turn over to cook.
Have plate ready.
Turn omelet onto dish.
Serves 4 or 6 people.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugars and water until you can form a ball in water. When syrup is almost done, beat 1 egg white until it forms a peak. Add a pinch of salt.
Pour syrup into egg mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix onion soup and sour cream.
Let stand one hour refrigerated.
Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain.
Fold sour cream mixture into spinach.
Season with nutmeg.
Turn into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits, water and salt.
Add cheese, margarine, eggs and milk.
Put in greased bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with crushed cornflakes and butter before baking.

title: charlotte's hamburger spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Cook spaghetti noodles. When noodles are done, mix ground beef, spaghetti, sour cream, Lipton onion soup mix, Ro-Tel tomatoes and shredded cheese. Cook in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: christmas candy
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add milk. Work in nuts and coconut. Shape into balls.
Chill.

title: brown sugar cookies(our favorite)
directions: Note:
Chocolate chips, nuts and oatmeal can be omitted if you prefer.

title: hot taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Cook noodles while meat is browning.
In large baking dish, layer with sour cream, add noodles then meat.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Heat in oven until cheese melts.
Add salsa and green onion on top.

title: cheesy veggie soup
directions: Simmer veggies in chicken broth until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Stir, then add cut up cheese slowly until it melts. When cheese is melted, soup is done.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Place apples and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 5 minutes longer on High.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute celery, mushrooms, onions, butter and green pepper.
Add bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Then add chicken.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixed together.

title: carrot, raisin and pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl. Add sugar. Add mayonnaise and mix well.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and serve 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: molded green salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and let set.
Mix together cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add jello, whipping cream and well-drained pineapple.
Fold in nut meats.
Pour into a jello mold.
Let set up completely.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: meat kabobs
directions: Mix lemon juice, oil, onion salt, pepper, curry powder, ginger, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce and garlic into shallow pan.
Add meat and mushroom caps.
Marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours or longer, turning meat occasionally.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients.
To serve, mix with hot water.
Use 2 teaspoonfuls per cup or to taste. Store remainder in tightly closed container.

title: zucchini gratin
directions: Pour 1/2 cup of milk over bread and soak several minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of olive oil, eggs, 1/2 cup grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Mash and stir with a fork until a batter consistency.
Add zucchini and rice.
Mix well and pour into oiled gratin dish. Press evenly all over and smooth surface with tines of fork.
Pour over the remaining milk, should barely cover surface.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dribble thread of olive oil over entire surface.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Break spinach into bite-size pieces.
Chill until crisp.
Make dressing by combining bacon drippings, vinegar, garlic, oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt or 17 Seasons.
Add pinch of sugar. Place crisp spinach in large bowl.
Add bacon.
Add sliced egg, if desired.
Toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, cranberry sauce, sugar, tapioca, lemon juice and cinnamon together.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes. Pour into bottom crust.
Cut 2nd pie crust into strips and crisscross (weave) strips on top of pie filling; brush with milk. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes, until crust is golden brown.
If edge of pie begins to brown too much, cover with aluminum foil to prevent overbrowning.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine margarine, honey, mustard, lemon juice and paprika; stir together well.
Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt and pepper. Put chicken pieces in Pam-sprayed 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour the honey mixture over the chicken.
Cover dish with foil and refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: golden pineapple sauce
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Combine juice and ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until boils and thickens.
Add pineapple and heat.
Spoon over chicken or ham.

title: mashed baked potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes soft and drain and mash until smooth, then add all the ingredients;
beat well.
If mixture seems stiff, add warm milk and beat well.
Cool and
put
in
a
buttered
casserole and
bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
You
can also put dots of butter on top.
This can be kept in refrigerator for a week.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine the tomato soup, sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, salt, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce with vegetables.
Marinate for 12 hours.

title: southern cobbler crust
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk; stir and pour over any kind of fruit.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.
Be sure a toothpick will come out clean when it's inserted.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Mix liquid ingredients.
Add all dry ingredients; mix.
Cook as usual pancakes.
A double batch works great with an 8 ounce flavored yogurt.
Makes great frozen pancakes to use as needed for little ones.
Just warm in microwave.

title: bob's peanut brittle
directions: Butter large cookie sheet.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread, stirring constantly.
Add raw peanuts. Continue cooking until syrup is golden brown.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla, butter and soda.
Stir well and pour onto buttered pan.
Cool and break in pieces.

title: salad supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O with 3 cups water.
Drain pineapple real good and save juice; then let Jell-O congeal.

title: fruit dessert(low fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix well and freeze for at least an hour.

title: souper tuna noodle bake
directions: In saucepan cook onion in butter until tender.
Put in rest of remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Top with sliced cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Cool and crumble into punch bowl. Spread drained pineapple over cake. Cover this with the pudding (made according to package directions) making sure sides are sealed. Cover this with the frozen strawberries. Ice with the Cool Whip.
Garnish with the pecans.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Spray a medium sized cake pan with Pam.
Pour in pie filling. In another bowl, fold softened butter and cake mix together. Sprinkle mixture over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage and noodles casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 4 cups water until tender. Brown sausage and onion; drain off excess fat. Combine soup, milk, 1/3 cup water and cheese. Blend well with noodles and meat.
Turn into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: romano fried potatoes
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic. Heat oil to 375°.
Dip potato strips into beaten eggs, then into bread crumb mixture.
Fry until golden brown on all sides.
Put in a baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for at least 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve hot.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water; add a little sugar to make it rise.
Combine hot milk with shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until shortening melts.
Cool.
Add well beaten eggs and yeast and mix well.
Add 1/2 the flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour. Mix thoroughly, but do not knead.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar.
Add the egg, buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Fold in the flour.
Add the rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: pour on pie crust
directions: Pour on top of sweetened fruit.
Bake at 450°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. Add the caraway. Add in the butter or margarine, buttermilk and raisins. Mix.
turn onto floured board.
Knead 1 minute.
Lightly butter a 10-inch skillet with flour or sugar (prevents sticking).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may top with milk, butter or egg white while baking.

title: my momma's potato salad
directions: Dice cooked potatoes; chop eggs, reserving 1 to 2 yolks.
Add pickles, ground mustard, white pepper and salt.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Sieve egg yolks on top of salad.
Top with paprika.

title: potato round casserole
directions: Brown and season ground beef and diced onion.
Add mushroom soup and soy or Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Place potato rounds on top of ground beef mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Serves 4.

title: almond bars
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar in electric mixer bowl.
Add egg yolk, almond paste and extract; beat well.
Add flour and beat just until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Smooth with a spatula into an ungreased 12 x 8 x 2-inch ovenproof baking dish.
Beat egg white until foamy and brush over surface of dough.
Scatter almonds over top.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass) for 40 minutes, until cake tests done.
Cool and cut into 24 bars.
Enjoy.

title: cookie cutter favorites
directions: Chill dough 3 hours.
Roll and cut.
Decorate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oregano batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Scald milk, then cool to lukewarm.
Add milk, sugar, salt, oregano leaves, egg, oil and 2 cups of the flour to the yeast.
Beat on high speed with electric mixer for 3 minutes. Beat longer if beating by hand. Stir in remaining flour. Set in warm place free from draft and let rise to double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: chicken a la king(low-fat)
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together chicken broth and peppers. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.
In a mixing bowl, gradually stir the milk into the flour until smooth.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Stir in canned mushrooms, chicken or turkey, pimento, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat through.

title: cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Steam or boil potatoes whole, 45 minutes or until done. Split, add butter and cheeses; salt and pepper.
Bake for 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; also season chicken while cooking with Lawry's seasoning salt, garlic salt and black pepper. After chicken is cooked, let cool and debone and chop chicken into fine pieces.
Heat cream of chicken and add green chiles.
Add small amount of water, approximately 1/2 can (small can).
Place chicken on tortilla close to edge; spoon chicken and chili sauce onto chicken and roll.
Place on cookie sheet.
After all are placed on pan, spread remaining sauce on top of tortillas and sprinkle mixture of cheeses on top.
Place in 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
